--BOUNDARY.21786536.2

I watched as Rob Hutchinson hammered "Re: 1 more MUI question :)" out on
their keyboard...

> [=> 
> [=>>   How do you open the MUI About window?.. I got a window with menus
> [=>> and stuff.. But the followindo doesn`t work:
> [=> 
> [=>>  MUIDoMethod 8,#MUIM_Application_AboutMUI,MUIObjLoc(1)
> [=> 
> [=>> Where 8 is the Application Object and 1 is the refwindow.
> [=>> Any ideas?
> [=> 
> [=> Why don't you use the "Aboutmui.mui" class?

> How`s that work then?.. I did try. Well, I opened a window
> and attempted to stick it in as a new object and my mig just guru`d :(
> I stopped it doing that.. And then gave up, cos I wasn`t sure I was even
> going about it the right way..

Looking at the C example for Aboutmui.mui it looks a bit complicated, but I
tried the muidomethod one and it worked fine.

MUIDoMethod APP,#MUIM_Application_AboutMUI,MUIObjLoc(WIN)

-- 
<sb>Rick Hodger - Programmer for #Pagan Software#
<sb>
<sb>Visit us at http://www.pagan-games.com
<sb>EMail us at /bloodline@pagan-games.com/
<sb>"Dafel: Bloodline" - The most acomplished RPG ever!
<sb>
<sb>ICQ:12861907 / IRCNet - #AmiGames - Rick
<sb>Team *AMIGA*
<sb>
<sb>If you understand something today, it must be obsolete.


--BOUNDARY.21786536.2
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="CrappyTest.ASC"
Content-Description: Rob Hutchinson <loki@sds.in2home.co.uk>


MUIApplicationTitle       "Testing"
MUIApplicationVersion     "$VER: Testing 18.0 (05.06.99)"
MUIApplicationCopyright   "Testing."
MUIApplicationAuthor      "Testing"
MUIApplicationDescription "Testing"
MUIApplicationBase        "TESTING"

;-- A ref win
;
MUINewObject 2,"Rectangle.mui",0

MUICreateWindow 3,"About","ABT",2
MUIAddSubWindow 3

MUIApplicationObj 8
If MUICreateApplication<>True Then End
MUIApplicationObj 0

MUINotifyApp 3,#MUIA_Window_CloseRequest,1,1

MUIOpenWindow 3

MUIDoMethod 0,#MUIM_Application_AboutMUI,MUIObjLoc(3)

Repeat
  ev.l=MUIEvent
  VWait
Until ev=1
End






--BOUNDARY.21786536.2

