@NODE "Mail_13" "Re: A BB2 -> Ascii converter, any ?"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 3 Jun 1999 03:27:23 +0100
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 02 Jun 1999 19:28:15 -0500
Subject: Re: A BB2 -> Ascii converter, any ?

Hi David

On 02-Jun-99, David McMinn wrote:
> 
>> Yes, he did.  Over 200 actually.  Somehow, the compiler is able to handle
>> them, but it gives my token-parsing routine fits - it reports the next
>> library number (in this case 16) and starts over at the beginning with
>>> 128...
> 
> I can't remember if anyone tested this at the time, but what happens to
> normal libs when you have a library next to it (in ID sequence) and what
> heppens with Mildred if another library has the number after Mildred?
> 
> Does Mildred suddenly turn into a reqtools lib? Or does the reqtools
> commands get the wrong token name/wrong command or the right token
> name/wrong command or the wrong token name/right command?

Well, that problem is sort of self-correcting, in a way.  The
Mildred.library is #15, and #16 is the Mini-Mildred.library - and of
course, you wouldn't be using both at the same time.

But I suppose if you installed some other library as #16 you would have some
bizzare problems...

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
