@NODE "Mail_14" "aaaaaaaghhh!!"
From: "Linda Bell" <zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: aaaaaaaghhh!!
Date: Sun, 13 Jun 1999 16:49:13 +0100
X-UIDL: bd03bb70d1afd1d410fa7bc91fc2fb21

Hello ppl,

Two probs:

ONE
This one is really, really, really, really, REALLY doing my head in.

If I run the following code on its own, after temporarily renaming the
translator.library to something else, it works perfectly.  But if I put it
AT THE VERY START of my program, TED leaves me with the PANIC! window, and
an executable just crashes.

WBStartup
FindScreen 0
If Exists("Libs:Translator.library")
  If Exists("Devs:narrator.device")
    NOP
  Else
    res=Request("Speaker","Can't find Devs:narrator.device"," :( ")
    End
  EndIf
Else
  res=Request("Speaker","Can't find Libs;Translator.library"," :( ")
  End
EndIf
End

TWO
I was checking out my OBJECT MAXIMUMS on the off-chance, and found
something weird.  Does anyone else have the following in theirs?

  WINDOWS       5
  s          5605
  ....                      ;more objects
  CONSOLES      5
  s             0

In fact - when WINDOWS is visible the first time I scroll down, there
is a null character before the s - but when I scroll down one more,
so that s is at the top, the null character disappears.

HUH?

I`ve installed new libs recently, but don`t know where this info is stored
by Blitz.

VIC





