@NODE "Mail_15" "Re: aaaaaaaghhh!!"
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Sun, 13 Jun 1999 21:14:05 +0100
Subject: Re: aaaaaaaghhh!!
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 7749baf1c79748ce8d36847c82bc2090

> If I run the following code on its own, after temporarily renaming the
> translator.library to something else, it works perfectly.  But if I put it
> AT THE VERY START of my program, TED leaves me with the PANIC! window, and
> an executable just crashes.

Wasn't there a bugged version of ElmoreDOSLibs (that's where Exists is from 
isn't it??). You could always try OpenLibrary_ and OpenDevice_ rather than 
exists, as that would be the correct way of doing it. Under low memory 
conditions, the files may be on disk, but if they have been flushed and can't 
be reloaded then using them will make things die.

> HUH?
> 
> I`ve installed new libs recently, but don`t know where this info is stored
> by Blitz.

Its read in by Blitz when it reads the libraries. Howevert, that s thing looks 
pretty screwed.


