Hi David

On 13-Jun-99, David McMinn wrote:

> Wasn't there a bugged version of ElmoreDOSLibs (that's where Exists is
> from isn't it??).

Errr, no, Exists is a regular Blitz command.

But this reminded me of something I've been meaning to ask, and never got
around to.

There is an "updated" version of the ElmoreDosLibrary on one of the BUMS -
but there were never any new docs.  The updated version is a much larger
filesize, and the command "ChDir" no longer works (but does tokenize) so I
just kept my old version.  I never had any problems with the old one...

(Yeah, I know you can use the command "Examine" instead of "ChDir" with the
new library - but why would I go and change my old sources, just to get a
larger exec size?)

Anyway, since the updated version is larger, I would think it must have a
lot of new commands in it?  Or was it just a mistake that it was included
on the BUM?

Does anyone have the docs for it?  Or any info on the new features?

