Hi David

On 09-Jun-99, David McMinn wrote:
> 
> 
> On 9 Jun 99, at 17:56, Sasu Lintula wrote:
> 
>> 
>> Hi all,
>> I have looked for acids chunky-library from everywhere but not managed to
>> find it.
>> Is it possible for someone to send it to me?
>> Thanks in advance,
> 
> I don't think it ever got past the beta stage and you can only use it in
> Blitz mode to AGA screenmodes.

Err, not quite true.  It's actually found in the Acidlibs that come with 2.1
Blitz.
And it does work in Amiga mode as well - I've tried it (the 8 bit stuff, I
never tried any of the 24bit commands)

You do need AGA or a GFX card to display the graphics.  It has a built-in
C2P for sending it to a planar bitmap, and WPA8_ also works with it.

I've attached the docs.

There is a nice chunky library in Fred's NCS also, which supports blitting
chunky shapes to the chunkies.

Although Mildred is much more capable then either of these, these are both
much easy to use and much smaller if you don't need all the special
effects.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



