@NODE "Mail_32" "AGA Laced Coplist."
From: Rob Hutchinson <loki@sds.in2home.co.uk>
Date: Sun, 20 Jun 1999 14:52:20 +0100
Organization: Satanic Dreams Software.
Subject: AGA Laced Coplist.
X-UIDL: 0462c233e1456e50d206f950346afb31

--BOUNDARY.274321248.3

Hello, and what not,

  I`ve been playing with the code David sent to the list, however,
I cant get it to display in 256 colours. 
I think it`s just displaying the first 128 or 64 cols, whatever, it
looks shite :(

Does anyone know why, I`ve attached the code, but it just doesn`t
work. I think it`s summat to do with the #Modulo spec, but I dont
know what any of it means :(

You need a 256 col 640x512 picture to run it.

Or did I just make some stupid mistake somewhere?

-- 
Rob,
This has been a message from, /Bogroll UK/, Have a shitty day :)
-- 
#EMAIL:# loki@sds.in2home.co.uk | #ICQ:# 27181384
#SDS FOUNDER:# URL: http://www.satanicdreams.freeserve.co.uk/
#PROJECT INFO:# Minimum Safe Distance [#--------- 10% ish]
#HOME OF:# /MorrisTheMaggot, CTTM2, TimeSwipe, NIB, BlitzBFB, Prefs2000 & TMS./
[ "Everyone is as God made him, and often a great deal worse." ]

--BOUNDARY.274321248.3
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="256Fuckup.ASC"
Encoding: binary

WBStartup
NoCli

#BPLMOD1=$108 : #BPLMOD2=$10A : #BPLCON0=$100
#BitMapSize=640
#Modulo=(((#BitMapSize-320)/8)-2)*2

;Build our user copperlist for Laced displays.
COP$=Mki$(#BPLMOD1)+Mki$(#Modulo)
COP$+Mki$(#BPLMOD2)+Mki$(#Modulo)
COP$+Mki$(#BPLCON0)+Mki$($f004)

BitMap 0,#BitMapSize,512,8
InitPalette 0,256
LoadBitMap 0,"Work:256_HRLACED2.ILBM",0

InitCopList 0,44,256,$11518,8,256,-20
DisplayUser 0,0,COP$

VWait 50 : BLITZ : CreateDisplay 0 : DisplayBitMap 0,0 : DisplayPalette 0,0 : Use BitMap 0

SetInt 5
  If Peek($dff004)<0
    DisplayBitMap 0,0,0,0
  Else
    DisplayBitMap 0,0,0,1
  EndIf
End SetInt

MouseWait
End




