@NODE "Mail_51" "Blitz code problem"
From: "Neil Bullock" <trogladite@trogsoft.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: Blitz code problem
Date: Fri, 2 Jul 1999 05:01:05 +0100
	charset="Windows-1252"
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: c45d32b329d66506db77d5c78d57b9fa

I'm updating my UnInstaller software, but I'm having some trouble with a piece
of code which deletes the actual files. Basically, the actual routine reads
through an UnInstaller script, and when it encounters a #filelist command, it
goes through this:

If LCase$(a$)="#filelist"
  a$=""
  Repeat
    a$=rline{}    ;Reads a full line of text in from a text file
    If LCase$(a$)="#filelist":Goto eds:EndIf
    If a$=Chr$(0):Goto enn:EndIf
    a$=Left$(a$,Len(a$)-1)
    If force=True:a$+" FORCE":EndIf
    a=Execute_("delete "+a$,0,0)
    If a=False
      Request "Error","There was an unknown error"+Chr$(10)+"while
uninstalling!","Ok"
      End
    EndIf
  Until LCase$(a$)="#filelist"
  .eds
EndIf

Here's the rline{} function if it helps

Function$ rline{}
SHARED fil

While i$<>Chr$(10)
  If Eof(fil):a$=Chr$(0):Goto en:EndIf
  i$=Inkey$
  FileInput fil
  a$+i$
Wend

.en
Function Return a$
End Function


But it seems to ignore the closing #filelist command in the script. If a
script read:

#filelist
c:LoadWB
c:NewCLI
#filelist
#nokill
#end

it would try deleting files called #filelist, #nokill and #end, and I can't
figure out
why it skips the closing filelist. Any help appreciated :)

