@NODE "Mail_56" "Re: Blitz code problem"
From: Leigh Parry <lparry@free4all.co.uk>
Date: Sat, 03 Jul 1999 07:45:04 +0000
Subject: Re: Blitz code problem
X-UIDL: 81072ab7a05f987a05417b261346c3ad

--BOUNDARY.18647000.1

Hello Neil

On 02-Jul-99, Neil Bullock wrote:
> I'm updating my UnInstaller software, but I'm having some trouble with a
> piece of code which deletes the actual files. Basically, the actual routine
> reads through an UnInstaller script, and when it encounters a #filelist
> command, it goes through this:

<Massive SNIP>

I took the liberty of changing the code, it should work better.
It use 'Edit$

-- 
<sb>
<sb>Leigh Parry
<sb>EMail: lparry@free4all.co.uk
<sb>URL: www.free0024068.free4all.co.uk
<sb>
<sb>Smile - People will wonder what you're thinking.
<sb>
--BOUNDARY.18647000.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="prog.asc"
Encoding: binary

; Return a lowercase line of text from the file opened (fil)
Function.s GetLine{fil}
  FileInput
  a$=LCase$(Edit$(256))
  PopInput
Function Return a$

; filelist code from prog

If a$="#filelist"
  finished=0
  Repeat
    a$=GetLine{fil}
    Select a$
      Case "#filelist" : finished=1                   ; finished the filelist
      Case ""                                         ; do nothing - blank line
      Default                                         ; any entries will be deleted
        If force=True:a$+" FORCE":EndIf
        a=Execute_("delete "+a$,0,0)
        If a=False
          Request "Error","There was an unknown error"+Chr$(10)+"while uninstalling!","Ok"
          End
        EndIf
    End Select
  Until finished=1
EndIf

; end filelist part


--BOUNDARY.18647000.1

