I've had no problems, ( the Re-Dimming of arrays )
I use an array of strings , which holds a 'page' of strings from a file.
Each page can be any amount of lines. So I Dim the array again before loading
the 'page' into the array.

I don't know the most amount of strings that will be in any one page ( as they
may be extended in future updates ) so i had to go with the re-dimming method.

Illegal ? , no eagles here to get ill ;-)

I have no Enforcer hits after 'Dim'ming the array again even after hundreds of
times, so it should be safe. 

Cya,

