@NODE "Mail_89" "C style strcmp & strcmpi"
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Fri, 2 Jul 1999 10:22:51 +0100
Subject: C style strcmp & strcmpi
X-UIDL: ade6c68fc5fc7e52425cf3530d2e4383

--Message-Boundary-12364
encoding: Quoted-printable
Content-description: Mail message body

Just two small functions I thought might be of use to some people. Its fas=
ter 
than doing if a$>b$ etc and you get three results for the price of one (a$=
<b$, 
a$=3Db$, a$>b$).


-- 
|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
 dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk
  http://members.xoom.com/David_McMinn
             ICQ=3D16827694
I used to have a handle on life, but it broke.



--Message-Boundary-12364
encoding: 7BIT
Content-description: Text from file 'strcmp.bb2'

; Description:      2 C style string compare routines in ASM
;                   one is case sensitive the other is insensitive
;
; Type:             System
;
; Last updated:     2nd July 1999
;
; Author:           David McMinn (dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk)
;
; In both functions, you pass the address of two strings you want
; to compare. The returned value will be:
;
; <0 if s1 < s2
; =0 if s1 = s2
; >0 if s1 > s2


; Case sensitive compare
Function.w ASM_strcmp{*s1,*s2}
.ASM_strcmp
        MOVEA.l d0,a0
        MOVEA.l d1,a1

'fetch: MOVE.b  (a1)+,d1
        MOVE.b  (a0)+,d0

        BEQ     'exit       ; check if letter is null terminator

        CMP.b   d0,d1       ; check if letters are same
        BEQ     'fetch      ; if they are, move onto next kletter

'exit:  ANDI.w  #$00FF,d0   ; make sure that top byte of word is clear
        ANDI.w  #$00FF,d1   ; make sure that top byte of word is clear
        SUB.w   d1,d0       ; get return result
        AsmExit
End Function


; Case insensitive compare
Function.w ASM_strcmpi{*s1,*s2}
.ASM_strcmpi
        MOVEA.l d0,a0
        MOVEA.l d1,a1

        MOVE.b  #96,d2
        MOVE.b  #123,d3
        MOVE.b  #$DF,d4

'fetch: MOVE.b  (a1)+,d1
        MOVE.b  (a0)+,d0

        BEQ     'exit       ; check if letter is null terminator

        CMP.b   d2,d0
        BLE     'noup1
        CMP.b   d3,d0
        BGE     'noup1
        AND.b   d4,d0

'noup1: CMP.b   d2,d1
        BLE     'noup2
        CMP.b   d3,d1
        BGE     'noup2
        AND.b   d4,d1

'noup2: CMP.b   d0,d1       ; check if letters are same
        BEQ     'fetch      ; if they are, move onto next kletter

'exit:  ANDI.w  #$00FF,d0   ; make sure that top byte of word is clear
        ANDI.w  #$00FF,d1   ; make sure that top byte of word is clear
        SUB.w   d1,d0       ; get return result
        AsmExit
End Function



--Message-Boundary-12364

