@NODE "Mail_98" "Re: Colour corruption"
From: Leigh Parry <lparry@free4all.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 29 Jun 1999 07:30:32 +0000
Subject: Re: Colour corruption
X-UIDL: fa1b539931c2a9c4e6b586c88d770b57

On 29-Jun-99, Sasu Lintula wrote:

> Hi,
> I'm converting my old game to work on a window. I've drawed blocks which
> uses colours from 8 to 15. The problem is that wb-palette gets corrupted
> when using my palette settings. Do I have to change all wished colours by
> using RGB? How can I restore original palette after closing window?
> 
> [Sasu Lintula]
> 

You could store the colurs B4 changing them and the reset them when exiting or 
use 'ObtainPen_' for colour matching a reserved pen colour.

Storing would only help if you don't use the workbench while your'e playing.

The 'ObtainPen_' method is a lot safer as those pens then get locked.
Mail me if you want an example,

Leigh
-- 
