@NODE "Mail_99" "Commodity Stuff"
From: "i03427" <i03427@selby.ac.uk>
Subject: Commodity Stuff
Date: Wed, 23 Jun 1999 11:34:12 +0100
Encoding: 7bit
X-Info: Selby College, England
X-UIDL: c1d462565147f49289ba4f5497148e81

A while ago, I asked about setting up a commodity using blitz, but I'm
having trouble. Someone sent me an example, and it was quite useful, but I
went and lost it. I seem to have lost most of my commodity code. So can you
answer these:

1) What command do you use to set the program as a commodity?
2) how can you check that your programs hotkey has been pressed, and how
can you set up a hotkey?
3) how can you read input from exchange, for instance telling your program
to quit or show it's interface, or whatever?

Thanks

Neil (sorry about the i03427 as my name)

