@NODE "Mail_100" "Re: Commodity Stuff"
From: Gareth Griffiths <gaz@jokerd.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 23 Jun 1999 19:04:36 +0100
Organization: Joker Developments
Subject: Re: Commodity Stuff
Encoding: binary
X-UIDL: 3dec521b764bff7ccedfc7ad161d1151

Hi i03427
On the 23-Jun-99 you said something about Commodity Stuff so now I am going to offer a witty retort (well maybe :)


PQ: A while ago, I asked about setting up a commodity using blitz, but
PQ: I'm having trouble. Someone sent me an example, and it was quite
PQ: useful, but I went and lost it. I seem to have lost most of my
PQ: commodity code. So can you answer these:

I only created my first commodity yesterday :)

PQ: 
PQ: 1) What command do you use to set the program as a commodity?

    success=MakeCommodity(name$,title$,description$)

     where name$ is what will appear in the CX list in exchange, and
    title$ and description$ are what is shown when you select that CX.

 2) how can you check that your programs hotkey has been pressed, and
    how can you set up a hotkey?

    success=SetHotkey(num,key$)

    e.g. success=SetHotkey(0,"lalt shift i") will create Hotkey 0 as
    Left ALT, SHIFT and I

    To read it put a 
  
     hk.l=HotkeyHit

    into your main loop, and test it using

     if hk.l=0 
      ....
     endif

    Where 0 is the number of your hotkey :)

PQ: 3) how can you read input from exchange, for instance telling your
PQ: program to quit or show it's interface, or whatever?

    put ex.l=ExchangeMessage into your mainloop

    and test using 

    if ex
         If ExchangeAppear ....
         If ExchangeDisappear ....
    endif

    etc.
PQ: 
PQ: Thanks
PQ: 
PQ: Neil (sorry about the i03427 as my name)
PQ: 

Its OK :)

PQ: ---------------------------------------------------------------------
PQ: To unsubscribe, e-mail: blitz-list-unsubscribe@netsoc.ucd.ie For
PQ: additional commands, e-mail: blitz-list-help@netsoc.ucd.ie
PQ: 
PQ: 

Sorry fot the crap layout, I just couldn't be arsed to set it out nice
