From: "Andreas Hĺkansson" <andy.h@telia.com>
Subject: Depth Scan
Date: Sun, 27 Jun 1999 13:45:43 +0200
X-UIDL: f119aac5c26ddc70c4498d6815ad418d

    Hiya!

I'm trying to make a small routine that scans a directory. I need a way to
make the routine scan the subdirectorys of the root dir, as well as scan
any subdirectorys it might find, until it's scanned threw the whole root.
What would be the easiest way of making such a routine? If you dont
understand what I mean, then think of it like a routine you would use to
find a file on your hd. You'd specify the root dir to start the scan and it
would scan threw all folders to look for files mathing your search criteria.

Now this is not what I'm doing, but the routine is exactlly the same. I know
all about reading/checking filenames and other info, it's just the scan
routine that can handel a hiarcy of folders.

Bye!





