On 27-Jun-99, Andreas Hĺkansson wrote:

C=I'm trying to make a small routine that scans a directory. I need a way to
C=make the routine scan the subdirectorys of the root dir, as well as scan

Hm, I guess its handy to know all the devices too(like when u press
`volumes` in the asl file/dir requester. I have NOT yet found a way to do
that. As for scanning a whole partition. I guess it`d go a bit like this:
scan for files in the root, then dirs, change to the dir which name appears
first in an alfabetically order. Do the same there. In the process you
should remember all dirs you find and put them in an array, When
you reach the end of the first dir you went in, perhaps following more
subdirs in that one, you go back to the starting point and take the next
dir(which is now in an array, so you dont need to scan the partition
again.) I guess the order wouldnt matter that much, as long as every dir
gets checked once, or not at all if found what u seek.

Hope this makes sense. 

Regards 

