Neil Bullock wrote:

> Can someone tell me how to get Blitz to check for the exitstence of a drive or
> assign without a requester appearing asking you to insert the drive?

Ok, in principle:

Lock the dos device list (There is a command to do this, ineither exec.library or
dos.library)
Scan through this linked list to see what devices are available
Free your lock.

But I'm not sure how to do thi exactly.  I tried it once but it just crashed my
machine.
Eventually I used the system Info command in C:, redirected the output o a
temporary file, read it in and parsed it and then deleted the temporary file.
Messy but it worked.  Lock_ still brought up requesters for me.

    Thom


