@NODE "Mail_123" "DiskFree"
From: "Linda Bell" <zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: DiskFree
Date: Wed, 16 Jun 1999 18:08:30 +0100
X-UIDL: ce6d278029604b81f9227185e48510c4

Hello,

I've just discovered a problem with the 'DiskFree' command - it returns
a value of 0 if you 'AnalyzeDisk "Ram:"'  Probably because Ram: is always
100% full.

My routine for checking available disk space, before saving a file, was:

  If f$
    AnalyzeDisk pa$
    Space=DiskFree
    gosub FigureFileSize
    if Space>EstFileSize
      ...

Now I've had to convert it to:

  If f$
    If (Left$(f$,9)<>"Ram Disk:") AND (Left$(f$,4)<>"Ram:")
      AnalyzeDisk pa$
      Space=DiskFree
    Else
      Space=MemFree
    EndIf
    Gosub FigureFileSize
    if Space>EstFileSize
      ...

Does anyone know a better way?

Thanks

VIC





---------------------------------------------------------------------
