Subject: Re: DiskFree
X-UIDL: 297e4a2ddb2c463506a77ad169f99914

Hi Vic,
On 21-Jun-99, Linda Bell wrote:
> James,
> 
> I tried that code concerning getting DiskInfo, but when I ran it, it said:
> 
> Ram:
> 
> Disk size: 108544
> Used: 108544
> 
> Am I missing something?

No, remember the RAM: disk is dynamic, so it is always full, or actually it
resizes itself to exactly fit the contents.

And even when you think it is empty, ENV: is stored there, and probably your
T: directory too.

Or did you mean you actually had more or less than that stored in it?

