Hello Linda.

You wrote:

> I tried that code concerning getting DiskInfo, but when I ran it, it said:

> Ram:

> Disk size: 108544
> Used: 108544

> Am I missing something?

MCP, it sounds like :o>

Anyway, on systems that havn't ptched the ramdrive.device (I think it is) you will allways be told that the RAM disc is the size of whatever is in it. However, you can easilly write to, it, nd wtch the size expnd. This is done so that yu don't get situtions like on the PC or ATARI, when you have to predetermin how much space you want to use for a Rm disc. The AMiGA just dynamically alloctes more memory, if more space is needed, and frees it, when it isn't needed anymore.  

Unless ofcourse, I am totally mistaken.


Greets,
