@NODE "Mail_130" "Re: DiskFree"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 22 Jun 1999 18:16:59 -0500
Subject: Re: DiskFree
X-UIDL: dd91c0401bad374a1adb9303fa56ef83

Hi Vic.

On 22-Jun-99, Linda Bell wrote:
> - no the point was that
> DiskFree states that there is no room in RAM to save my file, so I asked
> if anyone on the list knew a better way - as I assumed that it was because
> RAM is always 100% full - James sent me a routine - but it still seems to
> suffer the same problem.

OK, I see now.  Yes, the RAM: disk is always reported as full - so if you
want to see if there is enough room to save something there, just use
something like:

If AvailMem_ (#MEMF_ANY) > myfilesize.l

If there is enough free memory, the RAM: disk can use it to "save" your
file.


                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
