@NODE "Mail_138" "Re: Do...Loops"
Sender: tdc98@doc.ic.ac.uk
Date: Mon, 21 Jun 1999 17:34:55 +0100
From: Thomas Cobb <tdc98@doc.ic.ac.uk>
Subject: Re: Do...Loops
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 5a9b2a20c638d0b9430eea0784d81ff5

Gareth Griffiths wrote:

> Hi,
>    Is it possible to do a loop, with If...Then statements, without
> hogging the CPU? Like this:
>
> Repeat
>   x=Rnd(500)
>   If x=>100
>     ...
>     ...
>   EndIf
>   If x<=400
>     ...
>     ...
>   EndIf
> Forever

Stick a VWait in there - It'll put your program to sleep for a bit.  I
find VWait 5 gives the most free time without noticebly delaying my
programs reaction time, but if you are writing a commodity you could
probably get away with a longer delay.

    Thom


