@NODE "Mail_142" "DT-Pics"
From: Leigh Parry <lparry@free4all.co.uk>
Date: Thu, 01 Jul 1999 07:56:46 +0000
Subject: DT-Pics
X-UIDL: 68d3cea54e69288ec67253a4d148466c

Hello,

Yet another problem, I'm trying to use datatypes without using the RIDatatype
Lib but the example included in the archive of DoMethod.Lib (Picture example)
doesn't draw the picture to the screen it sets up, the palette is copied and
shown in it. Anybody got any thoughts on whats happening & a possible solution.

What I want to do eventually is to do a set of functions/statements that you
call to load a pic into a bitmap (With optional Remap/Pen Allocation)
which then also get freed again when calling a seperate function to do just
that.

Anybody done a Lib or code which does this ?

Erwan Fouret, says in the doc of the DoMethod Lib that a furture possibility
would be a lib to do this, Did he finish (or even start this).

TIA

Cya,

    Leigh.

