@NODE "Mail_148" "ECS/AGA Palettes"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Fri, 25 Jun 1999 13:36:15 -0500
Subject: ECS/AGA Palettes
X-UIDL: 96f430d453aed2a10a105b789db2d68b

Hi Everyone,

I want to make my program allow 256 colours on an AGA system, but limit it
to 8 or 16 colours on ECS.

The question is, is it possible to load a 256 colour palette on an ECS
machine?

Just the palette, I mean, the graphics will of course be the correct depth
as appropriate.

I have tested loading 256 colour palettes on my AGA system, then opening an
8 or 16 colour screen - it works fine.  In other words, the lower 8 or 16
colours of the selected palette are shown correctly, with no problems.

But will it work on an ECS system?  I'm not using any AGA-specific palette
commands. 

Later...
-- 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



