For additional commands, e-mail: blitz-list-help@netsoc.ucd.ie



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_149" "Re: ECS/AGA Palettes"
Date:  Fri, 25 Jun 1999 18:04:04 -0300 (ADT)
Sender: John Mason <ah210@chebucto.ns.ca>
From: John Mason <ah210@chebucto.ns.ca>
Subject: Re: ECS/AGA Palettes
X-UIDL: 1193814697517ebd67f09ed1b3b02185

Hi Curt,

> I want to make my program allow 256 colours on an AGA system, but limit it
> to 8 or 16 colours on ECS.
> The question is, is it possible to load a 256 colour palette on an ECS
> machine?
> Just the palette, I mean, the graphics will of course be the correct depth
> as appropriate.
> But will it work on an ECS system?  I'm not using any AGA-specific palette
> commands. 

I think the AGA chipset was designed so that its palettes would be
compatible with the OCS/ECS chipset, or at least I seem to remember
reading that somewhere.  You could always boot in OCS or ECS and find out
for sure.

-- 

