@NODE "Mail_152" "Enforcer-Pointercols, solution."
From: Leigh Parry <lparry@free4all.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 29 Jun 1999 07:24:44 +0000
Subject: Enforcer-Pointercols, solution.
X-UIDL: 6a668c2776982db219555fd8c4b014ac

Hello Mathias

On 28-Jun-99, Mathias PARNAUDEAU wrote:

>> Enforcer hits are caused by this code. ( AGARed ,etc.)
> 
> Yes, your program causes hits with my system too.
> 
>> How else colud i stor the pointer colours withouth having to go into too
>> much depth ( I might drown ;-)
> 
> I think I have a soluce but you have to catch the Wb palette.
> 
> <SNIP>
> 
> Good luck,
> 

I found a simpler solution.
Either move the WBenchToFront_ after the WBtoScreen 0
or put a Delay_ after the WBtoScreen 0

Probably something to do with the timing and AGARed not being on WB screen
properly, you can then also remove the 'dum=AGARed' command as it's no longer
needed as the folliwing AGARed returns the correct value.

Thanks anyway.

    Leigh
 
