From: John Mason <ah210@chebucto.ns.ca>
Subject: Existing files
X-UIDL: 8668c277590f5b291f27c48e8b10140d

Hi everyone,

  Does anyone know what the Right Way to check if a file exists is?  I've
been using Exists() from Blitz, but since it returns 0 if a file doesn't
exist, I can't tell if a file of 0 bytes exists or not, if you see what I
mean.  I've been looking though the autodocs but there isn't an Exists()
function from what I can see, it probably involves a combination of a few
different ones.

Thanks in advance!

--

