@NODE "Mail_155" "Re: Existing files"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 16 Jun 1999 21:44:54 -0500
Subject: Re: Existing files
X-UIDL: 7f28e0b4983bbbd9f8472d4ee5f77a6c

--BOUNDARY.1749222592.2

Hi John

On 16-Jun-99, John Mason wrote:
> Hi everyone,
> 
>  Does anyone know what the Right Way to check if a file exists is?  I've
> been using Exists() from Blitz, but since it returns 0 if a file doesn't
> exist, I can't tell if a file of 0 bytes exists or not, if you see what I
> mean.  I've been looking though the autodocs but there isn't an Exists()
> function from what I can see, it probably involves a combination of a few
> different ones.

Not much to it, actually.  But I think this will do what you want.  It
won't, however, give you the file size of the "found" file.

BTW, a file with a size of 0 bytes really doesn't exist, does it?   ;)

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1749222592.2
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="IsThere.asc"

; -- must use amigalibs.res
; -- checks for named file or directory
; -- returns -1 (True) if it exists
; -- or 0 (False) if it is not found


Function.b IsThere{filename$}
  *lock=Lock_(&filename$,#ACCESS_READ)   ;attempt to lock it
  If *lock                               ;yes, it is there!
    UnLock_(*lock)                       ;release it
    Function Return -1
  Else                                   ;not found
    Function Return 0
  EndIf
End Function


--BOUNDARY.1749222592.2

