@NODE "Mail_175" "Re: Files"
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Tue, 22 Jun 1999 14:32:54 +0100
Subject: Re: Files
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 7900d26d5e86fe55c86ea3f96d5b8d40

> Thank-q to those who helped me find the XBones Sound library. Is there a 
> good web site out there where I can find Blitz BASIC disks and libraries 
> archived. I still need to find this LEShapes library and copies of the 
> old BUM disks it seems before I can rebuild Blitz BASIC on my virtual Amiga.

No, you can't find the disks anywhere as you had to buy Blitz to get them. 
Unless someone is playing at naughty buggers.

Most of the 3rd party libraries are available in the dev/basic drawer of Aminet 
(http://de.aminet.net). There's also links to some on the Blitz 2000 website 
(self-plug) http://www.blitz-2000.freeserve.co.uk but its not complete, up-to-
date or anything, its just basically a copy of the old Blitz Basic Library 
page, which seems to have vanished.

You will struggle to find BUM disks without actually having them yourself - 
they were copyrighted. You might find bits of them around. BUM9 and 10 were on 
the Ultimate Blitz Basic CD, which also has the Blitz disks, BSS and BUI (a 
kind of BUM replacement).

> (my real Amiga is practically dead so I'm trying to get a virtual Amiga 
> working before it dies completely).

Want some Amiga bits?


