@NODE "Mail_178" "Re: Flickering display"
From: Mikkel =?iso-8859-1?Q?L=F8kke?= <flameduck@software.dk>
Date: Mon, 07 Jun 1999 13:28:11 +0200
Organization: M2 productions
Subject: Re: Flickering display
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: c5136581067b7eb81b9cd09fc6fdaa59

Hello Stephen.

You wrote:
> Hi all,

> I have a strange problem.  I've opened a cybergraphx screen 640x480
> 256colors.  I have a code loop that is something like this...

> Repeat
>    blah
>    blah
>    Change color values using AGAPalRGB 0,nn,rr,gg,bb
>    Show Palette 0
> Until Trigger is pressed

> The Show Palette command causes the display to have sporatic pixel
> flickering.

> Use Palette also causes this problem.  If I add WaitTOF_ or Vwait, the
> problem persists.

> Any ideas on how a can fix this?

I dunno, maybe:

Try using LoadRGB32_ *ScrVP,Peek.l(Addr Palette(num))

Where num is the number of the Blitz Palette object,
And *ScrVP is the pointer to the ScreenVeiwPort. If you hvn't got it, just do:

*ScrVP=ViewPort(scr)

scr offcourse being the screen number.

Or you could use the truncated form if you don't need  poointer to the Screens VeiwPoort:

LoadRGB32_ VeiwPort(scr),Peek.l(Addr Palette(num))

scr, is still the number of the Screen, and num the palette number.

This should work, allthough whether it fixes your problem is another matter entirely, since this may, or my not be the problem.


Greets,
-- 

