@NODE "Mail_186" "Four-play again"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Fri, 4 Jun 1999 18:22:16 +0000
From: "Linda Bell" <zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: Four-play again
Date: Fri, 4 Jun 1999 18:20:04 +0100

I`m sending this again, because no one replied - if no one replies to this
one, I`ll assume no one knows.

How do I test for lots of keys in Blitz Mode?

  Player 1 : Joystick port 1

  Player 2 : Joystick port 0

  Player 3 : Keyboard: Cursor-keys
                       RALT (FIRE)

  Player 4 : Keyboard: LSHIFT (UP)       OR     R      (UP)
                       LALT   (DOWN)            D      (DOWN)
                       E      (LEFT)            LALT   (LEFT)
                       R      (RIGHT)           LAMIGA (RIGHT)
                       LAMIGA (FIRE)            SPACE  (FIRE)

  Player 5 : Ctrl, LAMIGA, RAMIGA :)

I'll need to be able to test whether these keys are currently pressed
on each frame.


Thanks.

VIC

P.S. I`m ordering a 4-player joystick adapter tomorrow - or I would have
done, but Power Computing still haven`t replied to my mail.






