Hello Vic

On 04-Jun-99, you wrote:
> 
> How do I test for lots of keys in Blitz Mode?
> 
>  Player 1 : Joystick port 1
> 
>  Player 2 : Joystick port 0
> 
>  Player 3 : Keyboard: Cursor-keys
>                       RALT (FIRE)
> 
>  Player 4 : Keyboard: LSHIFT (UP)       OR     R      (UP)
>                       LALT   (DOWN)            D      (DOWN)
>                       E      (LEFT)            LALT   (LEFT)
>                       R      (RIGHT)           LAMIGA (RIGHT)
>                       LAMIGA (FIRE)            SPACE  (FIRE)
> 
>  Player 5 : Ctrl, LAMIGA, RAMIGA :)
> 

Is it not just possible to do this  {Not very tidy, I know} :-|

If RawStatus($x)=true
    Routine
End If

If RawStatus($y)=true
    Ho hum
End If

If RawStatus($x)=true
    La la
End If

Where x,y and z are the raw key codes for the keys u want to test 4.

A little hideous code, but should work.


 Regards

        Sandy Brownlee

