@NODE "Mail_195" "Re: Framerates of MonitorDrivers"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Fri, 18 Jun 1999 05:36:49 -0500
Subject: Re: Framerates of MonitorDrivers
X-UIDL: ab1bea4856ee7c4010a9eb258728a306

Hi Dave

On 17-Jun-99, Dave wrote:

> Just wanted to point out that after a while programming the pc, you
> rarely see any code checking the update rate of the display...all that
> usually happens is the game cycles are compared to seconds to get fps. I`m
> just wondering why we/you need the framerate. (ie, displaying a video..you
> know the fps, so you only need to count seconds). But then again, maybe I
> missed the point...

Sometimes it is handy to have some code executed by a VBlank interrupt. 
Then you don't need to worry about constantly checking the time in various
parts of your code to see if it is time to execute it.  Also, the interrupt
code will still continue executing even if the rest of the program is
"sleeping" while waiting for an event.

You also need to wait for the VBlank when doing double-buffering, to prevent
flickering.  So it's useful to know how often it will occur.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



---------------------------------------------------------------------
