Hello everyone,

I am now back on line.

To cut an extremely long story short, I installed some extra memory onto my
parents P.C.  Then Windows wouldn`t boot - I ran setup several times to no
avail, so then I formatted the HD and reinstalled windows.  Only to discover
that Windows disabled the Printer port and the Coms port.  Took me ages to
figure out how to fix it - something diabled them in the BIOS.  7 setups and
3 format/installs all together.

Anyway, I`m back up - though Freeserve have forced me to install Internet
Explorer 5 - I never realized Microsoft could think of even more ways to
annoy me.

At least this PC seems to run faster with 32mb.

Thanks to Curt for posting my message.

VIC



