@NODE "Mail_209" "Grand Theft AMiGA (Oh no, not again!)"
From: Gareth Griffiths <gaz@jokerd.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Sun, 06 Jun 1999 19:20:24 +0100
Organization: Joker Developments
Subject: Grand Theft AMiGA (Oh no, not again!)
X-UIDL: f2a4ce2834139a9f5c9e0937037fde07

--BOUNDARY.31928216.1

Hi,
   I recently started work on my GTA clone again. Previously I had
given up hope as I had no experience with map scrolling etc.

I still haven't.

This is my first bit of non-WB programming in blitz. It does NOT use
Blitz mode, 'cos some peeps said that if i did that, it would be
unfreindly to gfxboards etc.

My problem is this.

I have the car reacting to joystick movements, going forward, rotating
etc. But, when the car reaches about half way down the screen, it
starts to flicker horribly. 

The code is attached. The joystick rotation part is fairly simple, but
the code executed when you push up on the joystick is quite
longwinded, cos I didn't know any other way. Any ideas on this
gentlemen (and ladies, if there are any out there!)

I ain't using slices, just one screen and a bitmap.

The attached files are:

GTAtest.asc     -   ASC source code of the prog
GTAtest.bb2     -   Tokenised code.
GTAtest.xtra    -   ??? What do these xtra files do?
GTAcar.anbr     -   The car gfx (these are Lee Hesseldens. gta_dev.lha
on aminet)

Cya!
Gaz.
-- 
