Subject: Re: Grand Theft AMiGA (Oh no, not again!)
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 019f61d48198ad3931f8923cd523a53f

    Hi Gareth, 

> Hi,
>   I recently started work on my GTA clone again. Previously I had
> given up hope as I had no experience with map scrolling etc.

    You should use a 'Select/Case/EndSelect' instead of all your
If/Then... It's much faster.

    For a map scrolling the way to do it is easy:

    You have 16*16 blocks and you have an array of byte (or word
if you have more than 256 blocks) which describe your screen area.
So each array case = 16*16 pixel on the screen.

    For a 320*200 screen you will have: DIM area.w(320/16,200/16)
After multiply it by the number of screen you want horizontally
and vertically. 

    You could redraw all the block at each frame, but it will took
time, so if you wanna do a smooth scroll, declare an bitmap
of double withd and double height+16.
    
    BitMap 0,320*2+16,200*200+16,8

    Scroll the bitmap and blit the block previously the scroll.
If you do a scroll at 1 pixel per frame, you have 16 frames to
blit you block column.
    
        I hope this help,
          
-- 

                        Fred.

