@NODE "Mail_214" "Re: Grand Theft AMiGA (Oh no, not again!)"
From: "Linda Bell" <zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Grand Theft AMiGA (Oh no, not again!)
Date: Mon, 7 Jun 1999 18:34:48 +0100
X-UIDL: eb85e5b89b4b41139031ce2db3bb44a6

Anton wrote,

>you can't scroll the screen though- too slow- you'd have to
>use a Chunky bitmap with Mildred to do that.


I assume Anton means if you use blockscroll - well, you can scroll very
quickly without using blockscroll, ignore the examples given in the Blitz
manual and examples drawers - they`re too slow.  I`ve got a very fast
scrolling routine that I used with George2 - it`s not fast - it`s
supersonic.

I haven`t tried Mildred yet - I`ve got the archive, but not the room on my
HD to use it (as you are all no doubt aware by now).  However, I don`t think
that C2P can possibly be as fast as the routine that I use, because the
routine I use only blocks a maximum of 8 tiles (16x16) on each frame for a
50fps game to scroll 4-pixels at a time - and there is still masses of time
left.  In fact, Anton, if you read the readme that came with George2, you
should know how the routine works anyway - I can`t see any faster way of
doing it than that.

Gaz - if you want an explanation of how it works, mail me - I`m not trying
to put you off C2P - just offering an alternative solution.

VIC
zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk




