Hi Anton

On 07-Jun-99, Anton Reinauer wrote:
> On 08-Jun-99, V Bell wrote:
>> Anton wrote,
> 
>>> you can't scroll the screen though- too slow- you'd have to
>>> use a Chunky bitmap with Mildred to do that.
> 
>> I assume Anton means if you use blockscroll - well, you can scroll
>> very quickly without using blockscroll, ignore the examples given in
>> the Blitz manual and examples drawers - they`re too slow. I`ve got a
>> very fast scrolling routine that I used with George2 - it`s not fast -
>> it`s supersonic.
> 
>  On an OS screen/window? If you can I'd be /very/ interested! My game
> does hardware map-scrolling in Blitz mode, but superbitmaps in a window
> in AGA scroll horridly! :-) I've got it working in Qamiga, but I don't
> know how stable it is long term :-/

I once did some experiments with scrolling in Amiga-mode, by using an
oversized screen and bitmaps, and doing the scrolling by moving the entire
screen.  It worked nice and smoothly on my 030/50 with up to 128 colours. 

You can also duplicate Blitz-mode "slices" by using child screens so you can
have, for example, a scrolling game area on top with a stationary
"control-panel" on the bottom.

But I gave up on the idea when I discovered that GFX cards don't support
moving the screen.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
