Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 637845031262251e67454e54961949a2

--BOUNDARY.2013883064.3
Encoding: 8bit

Hello Gareth

Somewhere Gareth Griffiths wrote:

GG > I have the car reacting to joystick movements, going forward, rotating
GG > etc. But, when the car reaches about half way down the screen, it
GG > starts to flicker horribly. 

Solved that, but gained another problem, check the attached...

GG > The code is attached. The joystick rotation part is fairly simple, but
GG > the code executed when you push up on the joystick is quite
GG > longwinded, cos I didn't know any other way. Any ideas on this
GG > gentlemen (and ladies, if there are any out there!)

Don't use If ... Then ..., that burns cycle time.

E.G. -» If eggs=boiled then eat_them else let_them_boil

The compiler has to run run through the entire if line to see if there are any
exceptions or more code.

instead use 

If eggs=boiled
 eat_them 
 more_things_to_do_here
else
 let_them_boil
Endif

This way the compiler jumps to the next instruction/exception if the condition
is not what you needed...
-- 
Best Regards,

Rui Carvalho «gRiM»

