Subject: Re: Grand Theft Double Buffering
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: a8471992c2a5585bc51cf4dd06b866c4

Hi Linda

On 07-Jun-99, Linda Bell wrote:
> Rui wrote,
>> Don't use If ... Then ..., that burns cycle time.
>> 
>> E.G. -» If eggs=boiled then eat_them else let_them_boil
>> 
>> The compiler has to run run through the entire if line to see if there
>> are
> any
>> exceptions or more code.

> 
> Hmm. I`ve often wondered about this - I remember programming in Borland
> Turbo Pascal 5 - and there was an option to switch on Short-circuit
> boolean logic, so that the above wouldn`t happen - I wasn`t sure whether
> Blitz did or not - always intended to write a test program to time it -
> but have been using the method you mention in the meantime anyway. Why it
> doesn`t short-circuit is beyond me - it would seem the obvious thing to
> do.
> 
> VIC

I think it does this if you use a "Select / Case" rather than the multiple
"If/Thens"


Later...
