@NODE "Mail_235" "Re: GTCalc"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 2 Jun 1999 05:39:10 +0100
From: "Tony Rolfe" <edgewater@shoalhaven.net.au>
Organization: Edgewater Motel, Burrill Lake, NSW 2539 Australia
Date: 2 Jun 99 14:36:39 +1000
Subject: Re: GTCalc
Encoding: 7bit

On Mon, 31 May 1999 18:13:47 +0100 Linda Bell said:
> COOL IDEA #5375
> 
> Hey, ppl,
> 
> I've just had a cool idea for the new operating system for the Amiga:
> does anybody else think that it would be a good idea to update the
> integer gadget so that it can take operators?  This would be very
> useful in all sorts of areas - lets say you want to resize a picture
> in a word-processor to 2.5 times it's current size - you could simply
> click in the X/Ysize gadgets, and type "x 2.5" after its current
> values.  The OS would then calculate the total, and replace the
> current values.
> 
> Of course it wouldn't be able to be an integer gadget in this case,
> but you could tell it to drop/round the fraction.  Surely the OS
> could be written in such a way that Intuiton passes calculations to
> the maths libraries if necessary?  I don't want to have to run a
> calculator every time I want to know the exact figure I need - when
> this feature could be so easily incorporated into gadgets.  Actually,
> they could keep the integer gadgets, but add a new type that serves
> this purpose.  How about GTCalc?
> 

I just use GTString and parse the input  (at least I will when I can
get it working).  In fact, I use GTStrings for integer input so I can
output a meaningful error message rather than the system simply
beeping the screen.

Would be nice though, especially if it could handle more than just
simple arithmetic.

Cheers

-- 
Tony Rolfe
Amiga 2000, 68030/25, 1+4Mb
www.shoalhaven.net.au/edgewater

