> David McMinn wrote:
> 
> > > Environment is my guess.
> > >
> > > BTW, why is WB3.1 becoming OS3.5?
> >
> > Probably to symbolise a big update, but not major enough to be v4. Don=
't
> > know whay its called OS in stead of WB, cos only the WB is being updat=
ed
> > KS will still be 3.1.
> 
> Why did they skip OS 4?

OS 4 was going to be the developer OS which was due to come out before OS =
5 on 
the developer machines. It obviously didn't sound like a far enough advanc=
e, so 
they renamed it OS5dev and OS5prod (developer and production). And there i=
s 
stuff on the Amiga website saying that with all the updates to the classic=
 OS, 
they would make OS4 the last version number for that, seeing as we are alr=
eady 
at 3.5, that kinda makes sense.


-- 
