On 1 Jun 99 Linda Bell wrote about 'GTCalc'.

 LB> BTW, why is WB3.1 becoming OS3.5?

It's not, technically there is no such thing as WB3.1. The OS is numbered
as such, but Workbench uses it's revision, so OS3.1 is WB40.xx

In my case 40.42 and 40.68, but both are OS3.1.

Simon Archer


