@NODE "Mail_264" "Re: Hex Numbers"
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Fri, 2 Jul 1999 15:47:43 +0100
Subject: Re: Hex Numbers
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 3992eac649ec902c990d83ab2d49c7be

> > I'm messing on with hex numbers and want to know (simply??) how to
> > convert a decimal number into a hex number.....
> >
> > i.e. if I put 65536 into a function it should return $10000
> >
> > The hex$ function in blitz return 8 zero's ;((
> >
> 
> Not being anywhere near qualified to offer advice, but shouldn't it be
> 65565 since it starts from 0.

Blitz's hex$ function *should* be able to cope with long numbers (up to 
2,xxx,xxx,xxx ish). However, that was also said about the Val$ command ;)

Anyway, I presume you mean turn numbers into a hex string?
You can do this, but I haven't tested it:

Function$ tohex{a.l}
    For i.w=0 to 7
        c.l=a&$F
        if c<10 then c=c+48 else c=c+55
        b$ = chr$(c) + b$
        a = a LSR 4
    Next
    Function return b$
End Function

-- 
