Hi Everyone,

Further to my email regarding Hex numbers, I've solved that problem. But
it's lead me to another one.

I was using words instead of longs so it wouldn't return the correct Hex
equivilent. Now it does.

But how do I get Blitz to recognise this as a Hex number?

This number needs to be passed to a OS command for controlling AHI volumes,
so in the command you manually enter $10000 (full volume)

Now that works, but if I use

Val(Hex$(64*1024) 

or 

Val(Hex$(65536) 

which are the same, Blitz will obviously
think it's just a Decimal number (probably because of the VAL, but Hex$ by
iteself doesn't work either) i.e. 10000 being placed into the command but I need it 
to regonise it as a Hexadecimal number......

Any ideas?? The AHI docs state that the number passed must be a

    LONG Fixed; 16bits to the left of the point and 16bits to the right.

    Maximum Volume is 1.0 (0x10000L) or $10000 in Blitz terms
    Minimum volume is 0.0 (0x0L) or $0 in Blitz terms

Can someone please help with this?

-- 
Cheers,
    Daniel

