Then you're in trouble. For a hck that probabaly won't work on GFX crds, you can hack the system copperlist to use different sprite data. But I wouldn't recomend it. The OS (esp. 3.0) is very unstable afterwards, and the pointer will "flicker" if moved too fast (dunno why). Still it migght work for you. But really, there is no reason why you wouldn't want to have a window open....


