@NODE "Mail_287" "Re: Including a picture - with NCS-Libs"
From: Leigh Parry <lparry@free4all.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 29 Jun 1999 07:23:37 +0000
Subject: Re: Including a picture - with NCS-Libs
X-UIDL: d4d42cd3a39994843babfeda2e9635ee

--BOUNDARY.18586624.1

On 28-Jun-99, Frederic Laboureur wrote:

> 
>> I'll try a few small tests and let you know.
> 
>     Okay.. I'm curious.

Include is a test file (not particulary efficient)
    - when compiled length is 19976 (#SETVALUE)

and if you 'Join' a picture onto the end of it, when executed you get the
error 'Bad loadfile hunk'.

Anyone with any other solutions or fixes.
 
-- 
<sb>
<sb>Leigh Parry
<sb>EMail: lparry@free4all.co.uk
<sb>URL: www.free0024068.free4all.co.uk
<sb>
<sb>Smile - People will wonder what you're thinking.
<sb>
--BOUNDARY.18586624.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="join-tes.asc"


DEFTYPE .l

#SETVALUE=19976        ; length of this file' when compiled

WBStartup
WbToScreen 0
WBenchToFront_

NInitPicture 0
NInitScreen  0
NInitPalette 0
NInitBitMap  0
NInitPalette 0

*us.Task=FindTask_(0)
Prog_Name$=Peek$(*us\tc_Node\ln_Name)

suc=ReadFile(0,Prog_Name$)
If suc
  l=Lof(0)
  FileSeek 0,#SETVALUE
  pic$=Inkey$(#SETVALUE-l)
  PopInput
  CloseFile 0
  suc=WriteFile(1,"T:testpic")
  If suc
    Print pic$
    PopOutput
    CloseFile 1
    spic=1
  End If
End If

If spic=1
  If NLoadPicture(0, "T:testpic") >=0
    NGetPicturePalette 0, NPictureID
    If NBitMap(0, NPictureWidth, NPictureHeight, NPictureDepth)
      If NScreen(0, NPictureWidth, NPictureHeight, NPictureDepth, 0)
        NDisplayPalette 0, NScreenID
        NPictureToBitmap 0, NBitMapID
        NDrawingOutput NScreenRastPort
        NCopybitMap NBitMapID, 0, 0, 0, 0, NPictureWidth, NPictureHeight
      EndIf
    EndIf
  EndIf
  NMouseWait
EndIf

End




--BOUNDARY.18586624.1

