> > Include is a test file 
> > and if you 'Join' a picture onto the end of it, when executed you get
> > the error 'Bad loadfile hunk'.
> > 
> > Anyone with any other solutions or fixes.
> 
> This won't eliminate the extra memory usage, but I think you could IncBin
> the picture in the usual way, then use WriteMem to save it to T: 

Also, if Blitz were any use, you could specify that an IncBin'ed file should be 
put into chip (you can do it in C) when the program is loaded (I think it just 
needs an extra hunk in the exe). Then, when you want to display the picture you 
can use the copy that was part of your program, which is already in chipmem.

There might be something on Aminet for editing exe hunks.


