@NODE "Mail_290" "Re: Including a picture - with NCS-Libs"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 29 Jun 1999 18:43:36 -0500
Subject: Re: Including a picture - with NCS-Libs
X-UIDL: 56a6c01e79dbf97deac61edab4718b71

Hi David

On 29-Jun-99, David McMinn wrote:

> Also, if Blitz were any use, you could specify that an IncBin'ed file
> should be put into chip (you can do it in C) when the program is loaded (I
> think it just needs an extra hunk in the exe). Then, when you want to
> display the picture you can use the copy that was part of your program,
> which is already in chipmem.
> 
> There might be something on Aminet for editing exe hunks.

Or check the LoadSegment stuff in the autodocs.  But don't forget, an iff
picture is generally compacted so you can't just load it direct into chip
ram - you'd need to unpack it back to full size as you load it...

If it's a small picture, another way would be to store it in your program as
a set of drawing commands, then draw it and grab it off an undisplayed
bitmap.

Later...
-- 

