@NODE "Mail_291" "Re: Including a picture - with NCS-Libs"
From: Mikkel =?iso-8859-1?Q?L=F8kke?= <flameduck@software.dk>
Date: Thu, 01 Jul 1999 11:28:32 +0200
Organization: M2 productions
Subject: Re: Including a picture - with NCS-Libs
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 06d3a59c5bcd39a4e5a49942c1099364

Hello Christian.

You wrote:

> I found a use for the included picture, imagine you want a logo with your
> name, including it on the exe can prevent manipulations from bad guys

No it can't. The IFF header (FORM####ILBM) will still be there. Anyone, with even a slight knowledge of the IFF standard can easily rip it out, modify it, and paste it back in.

> A small 32k iff picture with an 8 colours logo eat a little of memory.

Well, it eats up 64k of RAM, that's twice the amount of loading it.

Now, here is the REALLY usefull way to use it:

1. Take your uncompressed ILBM picture.
2. LZ/RLE/XOR it so it isn't easily readable.
3. Load it into memory, and uncompress/dencrypt it.
4. Cludge it !

Anyway, I have some example LZ code here, which I'm gonna convert to Blitz, anyone have it allready, to save me the trouble ?


Greets,
-- 

