Hello John,


>Hi all,
>
>  I've been playing with IORequests and trying to read a chunk of data
>directly from my CD ROM drive (for the eventual purpose of playing CD
>audio).  All I have been able to get it to do is reset the drive -- when I
>try to use the CMD_READ command it just stops at that point forever.  I've
>pasted the code in below, if anyone can point out what I'm doing wrong I'd
>appreciate it!  Thanks in advance!


Hmmm..can`t see anything major (though I can`t test it here as I only have a
cd32 to use for my amiga cd), maybe you need something like BeginIO (for
async devices) and then wait till the request has been completed (like the
audio example I did a while back). Or maybe it`s the #CMD_READ, as each
device usually has it`s own special commands. Can you not use the CD device
(or is that the same thing?) and that seems to have #CD_READ (which equals
2) and #CD_RESET (which equals 1).

Just a couple of ideas,

Dave





