On Wed, 30 Jun 1999, Rui Carvalho wrote:

> Instead of atapi.device use scsi.device has most of those commands can only be
> performed in scsi devices (and has you know the amiga thinks your HD is a scsi
> as well has the CDRom!)

Yes, but with IDEFix the atapi.device is identical to the scsi.device
AFAIK.  I think the problem is to do with not having the correct commands,
because once I solved the problem with it stopping after sending the
command, I got a command not supported error or something like that.
The problem with the code, BTW, was that I was passing the address of the
pointer intstead of the pointer itself (arrgh!).  I guess what I need is a
whatever #includes (or the Blitz equivalent) define standard ATAPI/SCSI CD
commands.

