--BOUNDARY.21791752.3

I watched as Mikkel Lokke hammered "Re: IORequests" out on their
keyboard...


>> Instead of atapi.device use scsi.device has most of those commands can
>> only be performed in scsi devices (and has you know the amiga thinks
your
>> HD is a scsi as well has the CDRom!)

> The problem here I think is that scsi.device doesn't recognise the
> AT/ATAPI cdrom drive. (Maybe on OS3.1 ?)

It should do...

scsi.device on an IDE amiga - interprets the scsi commands into the
appropriate IDE commands and passes them onto the IDE device

scsi.device on an SCSI amiga - passes commands straight to the SCSI device

atapi.device on an IDE amiga - interprest the scsi commands into the
appropriate IDE/ATAPI commands and passes them onto the IDE device

...technically all you ever have to do is use SCSI commands in a system
friendly manner and it should all work.

The attached should work perfectly with ALL CD-ROM drives ATAPI, SCSI or
IDE - and doesn't require any additional libraries. (Runs from a shell)

NOTE: You need to type in the device name *exactly* as it is named in your
devs: directory.  For Example, Atapi.device should be typed as such and
*not* atapi.device.  YOU HAVE BEEN WARNED!

The result should look like this:

<sb>
Ram Disk:T> test

Blitz2 SCSI/ATAPI CD COMMANDS TEST

Device: ExpXDS.device
Unit: 4

Opening ExpXDS.device, unit 4...DONE!
Valid CD in drive!

1 / CDDA / 150-13190
2 / CDDA / 13190-32687
3 / CDDA / 32687-45882

Playing track 1 (LMB to quit)...
13201

Ram Disk:T>    

