@NODE "Mail_313" "I`m gonna take up C again"
From: "Linda Bell" <zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: I`m gonna take up C again
Date: Tue, 22 Jun 1999 19:34:01 +0100
X-UIDL: 4908a8126fc3c61bb9e0922101f0175d

Can anyone tell me why the following keeps crashing, if I temporarily rename
the translator.library, and reboot.

WBStartup
FindScreen 0
lib$="translator.library"
*mylib.Library=OpenLibrary_(&lib$,37)
If *mylib
    CloseLibrary_ *mylib
Else
    BeepScreen 0
    End
Endif
End

Every attempt that I have made to determine whether the translator.library
exists (when i know that it doesn`t) has caused my Amiga to crash   Does the
above crash your system - after renaming your translator.library, and
rebooting?

VIC




