@NODE "Mail_314" "Re: I`m gonna take up C again"
Date: 	Tue, 22 Jun 1999 17:37:58 -0300 (ADT)
Sender: ah210@chebucto.ns.ca
From: John Mason <ah210@chebucto.ns.ca>
Subject: Re: I`m gonna take up C again
X-UIDL: 5f276c29a1524abfcbca763f163aebff

On Tue, 22 Jun 1999, Linda Bell wrote:

> Can anyone tell me why the following keeps crashing, if I temporarily rename
> the translator.library, and reboot.
> WBStartup
> FindScreen 0
> lib$="translator.library"
> *mylib.Library=OpenLibrary_(&lib$,37)
> If *mylib

This might be your problem.  If this was C, it would be correct, but since
in Blitz "true" is -1, instead of any positive value like in C, you won't
get the results you're after.  However, this should just always fail, not
crash!  

I just made this code, which works fine here:

--

lib.s = "translator.library" 

*lib.Library = OpenLibrary_(lib, 37)
If *lib > 0
  Request "Message","Library opened okay","Ok then" 
  CloseLibrary_(*lib)  
Else
  Request "Message","Couldn't open library","Ok"  
EndIf

--

I don't have the courage to risk crashing my system right now so I won't
try yours just now :)

Hope this helps,

-- 

John Mason   --   ICQ 17931257
http://chebucto.ns.ca/~ah210/Profile.html
