Righty then - this DOES work. Wehey :)

But i now have yet another problem - Sometimes it can read multiple key
presses and other times it cant - i found out that this depends on what keys
you want pressed together. The code i am using is this:

Repeat

    If RawStatus($4F)=-1 AND RawStatus($20)=-1 AND SPEED>((MAXSPEED/2)-2)
Then A=A-1 : Goto FWD
    If RawStatus($4E)=-1 AND RawStatus($20)=-1 AND SPEED>((MAXSPEED/2)-2)
Then A=A+1 : Goto FWD
    If RawStatus($4F)=-1 AND RawStatus($31)=-1 AND SPEAD>((MAXSPEAD/2)-2)
Then A=A-1 : Goto REW
    If RawStatus($4E)=-1 AND RawStatus($31)=-1 AND SPEAD>((MAXSPEAD/2)-2)
Then A=A+1 : Goto REW

    If Inkey$=""
        <stuff>
    EndIf

Forever

With this code, when you press "A" and the Left-Arrow key the variable A
will decrease by 1 and then goto a subroutine called FWD. When you press "A"
and the Right-Arrow key A will increase by 1 and goto FWD. When you press
"Z" and Left it will make A go down 1 and then jump to REW subroutine and
when you press "Z" and Right A will go up by 1 and the jump to REW.

Well at least it is meant to. All of it works fine apart from when you press
"A" and right, it does the <stuff> part in the If Inkey$="" bit!

How do i get around this - I think it may be the use of the Inkey$ command
but i dont know anyother quick way to see if there are NO keys pressed.

Please help.

