Hi David

On 01-Jul-99, David McMinn wrote:
> Hi folks,
> 
> I think I managed to obtain every library released for blitz (not
> including system libs that have been fd converted) and there's 97 of the
> damned things. Quite impressive I thought.
> 
> Anyway, I'd like to know if any of the library tools that are going around
> can scan for clashing tokens? I know there are a few clashes, but I want a
> list and can't be arsed checking every bloody library.

Use BlitzLibMan - it's on the UBB CD, in one of the BUM's, I think.  It's
also on my web site.

It will give you a complete list of all libraries with their numbers when it
starts up, and highlight any clashing library numbers.  It also lets you
select which libraries you want to include (or not include) in your deflibs
file.

Later...
