@NODE "Mail_352" "Re: Lookup-tables"
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Mon, 7 Jun 1999 18:30:21 +0100
Subject: Re: Lookup-tables
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 9f5e787d4bffd76c11fce7951f1a6930



> Hi,
>    Umm. What is a lookup-table?

An array that contains pre-calculated values. Normally to gain speed, or 
because the values are uncalculatable during the program for some reason. An 
example would be to use an array 360 elements in size to store the values for a 
sine wave, saves you having to calculate a value during each loop or something, 
therefore more speeed.


