Well, it sounds like Intuition is keeping track of where the gadgets ar, a=
s you 
can click on them in the place they are supposed to be. Given the fact tha=
t the 
windows can be split like the picture above (which can't be done by intuit=
ion, 
i.e. you can't open a window off screen) it sounds like it is a case of th=
e 
display getting corrupted (duh, obviously).

Maybe the way you open your screen causes it to have problems later, as it=
 
sounds like a bitmap pointer or some display registers are getting changed=
 
somehow. As you can tell, I have no idea what I'm speaking about.


