Possibly.  I've never had any users tell me about this.

Anyway, I was able to cause it to happen by running my chip memory down to
less than 150k, then changing the card images. This frees all the card
shapes, then grabs a new set from an iff picture.

I've attached a couple of screengrabs. Sorry about the large filesize, but a
picture is worth 1000 words, so these take the place of 2000 words of
explanation  ;)

The first shows is what it looks like to me, with the menu window out of
place -

The second is the actual screengrab made with PPaint, which shows the menu
window in the correct position, but the main window split in half...

It looks like the main window is being moved (or having it's pointers messed
up) although the visual effect seen by the user is the opposite.

Oh, and doing a window grab from PPaint also grabs the menu window
correctly, but the main window split in half like picture 2.

Later...
-- 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
