@NODE "Mail_374" "Re: Monitor Tricks"
From: Rick Hodger <rick.thehub@bigfoot.com>
Date: Thu, 24 Jun 1999 17:50:48 +0100
Organization: Pagan Software
Subject: Re: Monitor Tricks
X-UIDL: 8b5a01d86f41f3e6112001d204c7a13c

Hello fellow U-Nutter...

> I have a fancy power saving monitor and I know that the power save modes
> are activated when the Vertical sync is below 50Hz. How can I get blitz
> open a blank screen with a VSync < 50Hz?

Haven't a clue mate, but I think MCP can trigger the monitor power saving
modes....not really sure tho

> Also, does anyone know how to put an IDE HD into power save mode?

Yes, you send a #SCSI_CMD_SSU (SCSI COMMAND START-STOP-UNIT) to the drive
with a value of 0x2 to stop it, and 0x3 to start it up again.  It's the
same command you would use to open and close a CD-ROM drive.

-- 
