@NODE "Mail_375" "Re: Monitor Tricks"
From: Rick Hodger <rick.thehub@bigfoot.com>
Date: Thu, 24 Jun 1999 17:54:37 +0100
Organization: Pagan Software
Subject: Re: Monitor Tricks
X-UIDL: 057b312233a092d8930b9276af5de625

I watched as David McMinn hammered "Re: Monitor Tricks" out on their
keyboard...

>> WARNING! These power saving modes for HD's will reduce the life of the
>> HD. I've lost 2 HD's at work because of this one of which was on the
main
>> server...

>> DO not use IDEFIX feature to turn off the HD motor...

> Isn't it more to do with the Amiga version of IDE?

Nope, it just causes a LOT more wear and tear on the drive motors.  You're
only really supposed to use if the computer isn't going to use the
hard-disk for a couple of hours, like you were rendering a massive picture
in memory...then it would be safe because the wear and tear of the motor
running for a few hours would be a lot less that stopping and starting it.

> Anyway, you weren't supposed to say that, he won't break his HDD now ;)

I haven't seen a HD break down from this, but that's not to say it won't
happen :)

-- 
