@NODE "Mail_377" "Re: Monitor Tricks"
From: Donovan Reeve <bubby.lnk@ispi.net>
Date: Thu, 24 Jun 1999 21:47:15 +0500
Subject: Re: Monitor Tricks
X-UIDL: f4a40c270205367d2ddcb82ec956e05b

On 24-Jun-99, Rui Carvalho flashed:
>Hello David

>Somewhere David McMinn wrote:

>DM > As for the IDE drives, it is possible as IDEFix does it. But I don't
have
>DM > no info.

>WARNING! These power saving modes for HD's will reduce the life of the HD.
>I've lost 2 HD's at work because of this one of which was on the main
>server...

>DO not use IDEFIX feature to turn off the HD motor...



  Rui's right!  Starting up puts far more stress on both the motor and
bearings of a hard drive than hours of spinning at speed, and causes the
heads to seek also so adds wear and tear to the head control selenoids
and pivot bearings also.  Since attempting to save power by powering
down whenever not being accessed causes many more start-ups than normal
useage, your drive will surely fail much sooner.  Take Rui's advice
and don't try to conserve (what after all would amount to an insignificant
amount of) power at the much greater expense of your drives.


cacha later,

Donovan Reeve (bubby.lnk@ispi.net)



