@NODE "Mail_383" "MUI Help Please ;)"
From: Daniel Allsopp <daniel@thesnakepit.demon.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 16 Jun 1999 03:06:05 +0100
Subject: MUI Help Please ;)
X-UIDL: f291e94c917265e5c354a50bb5770b07

Hi everyone,

I've been trying to find out what object is current selected in the TAB
CycleChain.

When the user hits TAB the little white box moves around the selected
objects which you've set, how do you find the number of this object, i.e.
the Blitz reference number.

I've got a pointer so far used like this :

    *object_active=muiget(#WINDOW,#MUIA_Window_ActiveObject)

which does change when the currently tabbed item moves. So what I really
need is a command opposite to MUIObjLoc().

Something that takes a pointer of an object and returns the number you
assigned it when creating the object.

If that's not possible how about reading the contents of the selected
object, using #MUIA_Text_Contents? in fact that would be better but the
current MUIGet command only uses the number of the object, not a pointer ;((

Back to square one

Anyone got any ideas?

-- 
Cheers,
    Daniel

<tsb>E-Mail: daniel@thesnakepit.demon.co.uk
<tsb>URL: http://www.thesnakepit.demon.co.uk/
<tsb>ICQ Number : 20783863
