@NODE "Mail_386" "Re: MUI List views (again Grrrrrrr)"
From: Andrew Wheeler <apwheeler@apwheeler.demon.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 09 Jun 1999 23:17:19 +0100
Subject: Re: MUI List views (again Grrrrrrr)
X-UIDL: 35902a051447641411ddd9785dfcfe36

Hello S9225796

On 09-Jun-99, S9225796 wrote:
> Hello everyone. I'm having to problems with those god damn MUI List
> Views.
> 
> 1. I've got a list with a few available selections and I wish for the
> user to be able to click on one of the items and for the list view to
> return a value stating which item was clicked. Any ideas? I've had a
> gander at the autodocs, however the tags do not seem to work :(

usersel=MUIGet(#lists1,#MUIA_List_Active)

whereas usersel equals the returned position of where the list is selected, -1
means no item is selected.  #lists1 is the object number of the List

> 
