    ImageButton.mcc
    InfoText.mcc
    Lamp.mcc
    LayGroup.mcc
    MailText.mcc
    MathString.mcc
    MimeEditor.mcc
    NFloattext.BB2
    NList.BB2
    NListView.BB2
    Pkb.BB2
    Readargsgroup.BB2
    SettingsWindow.BB2
    TableGroup.BB2
    TearOffBay.BB2
    TearOffPanel.BB2
    TextEditor.BB2
    TextInput.BB2
    ToolBar.BB2
    TransferAnim.BB2
    TWFmultiLED.BB2

So I`ve decided to release the whole lot as MUI2.RES :)..

The new MUI res has now got Freds NCS Amigalibs.res included in it
instead of the original Blitz2 one and includes all the original MUI
stuff. But now has all the above converted mcc`s Constants, macros and
Newtypes.. (It`s now a bloody great 418,384 bytes!!!) WOW!

I`ve also included my StackAppending code as a Macro, which can
be called as just:

 !StackOpen{12000}

And just before the #End# command:

 !StackClose

It seemed a little simpler :).. Though I dont know how legal this is..
If there are any problems with it, I will remove it, but it works
fine for me!

There is also an example of using TextEditor, ToolBar, HexEdit, 
BetterString and InfoText in there too :)

I will update this Resident regularly, as new MCC`s and updates become
availible. I will also add a lot of small examples and probably convert some
of the C examples that come with the MCC`s. Please contact me if I`m missing
some MCC`s or newer versions are available.

<tsb>

If you want it (even if you dont and you code MUI apps I suggest you get it)
You can get it from:

  http://www.satanicdreams.freeserve.co.uk/

In the downloads section. Which coincidently has just been updated :) heheh
PLUG PLUG PLUG :)
Hope this is as useful to you as it is to me..
And thanks to David McMinn for help with some C translations :)

<tsb>

Lastly, Fred if you dont want the NCS resident compiled into the MUI res
I will recompile with the crappy original, but I think it`s better that
people use the correct variables :).. And I gave you a big mention :)

CHOW ...

Cya!
