>In the meantime, I`m updating my first ever program, which uses the
>speak-handler, and the narrator device.  When I quit the program, these two
>objects are still in memory.  Does anyone know if there is a way to find 
>out
>if any other program is using them, and if not, shut them down?
>
>While I`m at it, the same goes for fonts.
>
>Thanks
>
>VIC


I know that in Amiga DOS it is possible to 'dismount' a device by using the 
command:

    "mount xxx.device remove"

Although I am a beginner at Blitz Basic (one of the reasons I joined the 
list) I was thinking that perhaps there is a similar way of doing this in 
Blitz.

Just an idea.

Jamffrey. (jamffrey@hotmail.com)

