OK, I've finally gotten it to work.  It's OK if I put Ashley's dosDriver
into my DEVS/DosDrivers drawer - so the speak-handler is mounted on bootup.

But for some reason, it won't work if I try to mount the speak-handler
later.
Maybe SetPatch or something else changes the vectors afterwards, or possibly
one of my patches screws things up.  Anyway, this seems to be the cure for
anyone else who has this same problem.

Thanx again  :)

BTW, Vic, this would indicate that it is NOT a good idea to have your
program try to remove the speak-handler.



