If you`re any good with using os calls, you can use the newtype

  .narrator_rb

to set the channels - as well as other stuff that I want to access, but am
crap with OS stuff.  I`m working on a SAY_IT_BETTER program that allows you
to set the voice using slider gadgets and stuff (rate, pitch, frequency,
etc)- but to get to the new cool stuff (perturb, etc.), I have to use the OS
routines - but Translate is untokenized after I open the tranlator.library.
I think I can do it with VoiceLoc - but I can`t #CMD_Reset from Blitz to
flush the current speech -

This program also allows you type in phrases, and save them to disk, along
with the voice presets - as after writing Mr. Wolf - my cheeky speaking
clock - it occurred to me that speech is very underused - possible uses are:

Calculators that read your input to you so that you don`t have to look at
the screen.

Multiplayer games - as you said.

Monkey Island type games with speech - as you can get all sorts of voices
with it.

There are loads of ways to get inflection in the sentences, and I was hoping
that this util would be very useful for people to mess with if they were
thinking of including speech in their progs.

VIC





