@NODE "Mail_416" "Re: narrator.device - furthermore"
From: Donovan Reeve <bubby.lnk@ispi.net>
Date: Mon, 14 Jun 1999 18:44:57 +0500
Subject: Re: narrator.device - furthermore
X-UIDL: 440e9ec05a3e082b879889409da2a7ae

On 13-Jun-99, Linda Bell flashed:
>> Check out:  http://www.amigaprog.freeserve.co.uk/files/
>>
>>  There's some updated docs on the narrator.device with all the SetVoice
>>stuff and translator lib.


>Thanks Anton,

>In the meantime, I`ve been looking at the Autodocs again, and I want to use
>OS calls instead of the Blitz commands - but it refers me to the Libs and
>Devs volume of the Rom Kernel - which I don`t have - does anyone have it -
>it will have to be revision 2 as I think it was dropped from WB 3.0 - don`t
>know why!


  Yes, the speech was all droped from AmigaOS3, because Bell labs (who made
Amiga speech system) wanted to much for the rights to use it in the (then)
new OS, and WAY more than C= wanted to pay to improve it.  It is worth
buying WB 2.x to get it for those who don't have it.

  If anyone is interested, Parth Galen software make some EXCELLENT tools
for speech developement and useage.  You can even develope your own
replacements for the Amiga devices if you are willing to work at it.
It is possible to develope systems for any type of accent and language,
including both new devices and librarys.  It is not for the faint of
heart though.


cacha later,

Donovan Reeve (bubby.lnk@ispi.net)



