Donovan Reeve wrote:
> >In the meantime, I`ve been looking at the Autodocs again, and I want to use
> >OS calls instead of the Blitz commands - but it refers me to the Libs and
> >Devs volume of the Rom Kernel - which I don`t have - does anyone have it -
> >it will have to be revision 2 as I think it was dropped from WB 3.0 - don`t
> >know why!
> 
>   Yes, the speech was all droped from AmigaOS3, because Bell labs (who made
> Amiga speech system) wanted to much for the rights to use it in the (then)
> new OS, and WAY more than C= wanted to pay to improve it.  It is worth
> buying WB 2.x to get it for those who don't have it.

I don't know if everyone knows this fact already (Mr S. Walker
probably does!) but the Psygnosis game WipEout 2097 features the
Amiga speech in its full glory. They certainly added some reverb
to the voice and it's obvious they didn't use it because it
sounded 'realistic' but it worked perfectly in this situation.
As you were hurtling along at full pelt, another racer on your
rear gaining ground, suddenly you hear the word 'Missile' (or
perhaps that be 'MIHSAY3L') and before you know it you're hit!

The funny part was the "Credits" sequence scrolling up the screen
at the end of play, where (on the PlayStation version at least)
it lists "Speech: Amiga 1200". It may not have looked so 'cool'
if the credits were to Bell labs.

Cheers,

Paul

-- 
< Paul Burkey http://www.sneech.freeserve.co.uk >


