@NODE "Mail_431" "Re: narrator.device - v37 features"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 17 Jun 1999 07:01:09 -0500
Subject: Re: narrator.device - v37 features
X-UIDL: 229e7412544501652dd8f07c610c81cb

--BOUNDARY.1748545192.1

Hi Everybody,

I found an example on an old BUM which shows how to access the new features
of the v37 speech stuff.  

I fixed it so it works right, and I'm posting it for anyone who is
interested.
With this and the SetVoice command, you can access everything except the
left/right channel assignments without having to go through the OS.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748545192.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="speechtest.asc"

;by Curt Esser
;camge@ix.netcom.com
;June 17 1999

;a quick demo showing how to use the added v37 narrator features

;modified from an example found on BUM 2

;reqiures the v37 or better narrator.device
;and the v37 or better translator.library

;if you have problems with recoverable alerts or crashes after
;installing the v37 speech stuff, try also installing the
;speak-handler in your sys:l/ directory, and mounting the
;speak-handler on bootup.

;to get a feel for all the new features available, try the program
;SpeechToy2 found on Aminet


NEWTYPE.newvoice
 flags.b        ; 1 to access these features or 0 to ignore them
 F0enthusiasm.b ; pitch difference 0 ~ 255  Default=32
 F0perturb.b    ; wurble in voice  0 ~ 255  Default=0
 F1adj.b        ; F1 pitch  (low)  +/- 100  Default=0
 F2adj.b        ; F2 pitch  (mid)  +/- 100  Default=0
 F3adj.b        ; F3 pitch  (hi)   +/- 100  Default=0
 A1adj.b        ; amplitude (low) -31 ~ 32  Default=0
 A2adj.b        ; amplitude (mid) -31 ~ 32  Default=0
 A3adj.b        ; amplitude (hi)  -31 ~ 32  Default=0
 articulate.b   ; emphasis         0 ~ 255  Default=100
 centralize.b   ; centralization   0 ~ 100  Default=0
 *centphon      ; must be  IY IH EH AE AA AH AO OW UH ER or UW
 AVbias.b       ; AV bias         -31 ~ 32  Default=0
 AFbias.b       ; AF bias         -31 ~ 32  Default=0
 priority.b     ; Priority while speaking   Default=100
 pad1.b         ; just for alignment
End NEWTYPE

Spk$="COME ON EVERYBODY,DANCE?"

;--
cent$="AO"
*nar.newvoice=VoiceLoc   ;find the structure's address
*nar\flags=1             ;and access the v37 features
*nar\F0enthusiasm=32     ;here we set all to the defaults
*nar\F0perturb=0
*nar\F1adj=0
*nar\F2adj=0
*nar\F3adj=0
*nar\A1adj=0
*nar\A2adj=0
*nar\A3adj=0
*nar\articulate=100
*nar\centralize=0
*nar\centphon= &cent$
*nar\AVbias=0
*nar\AFbias=0
*nar\priority=100

NPrint "Found VoiceLoc at ",*nar
NPrint "All set to defaults"
Speak Spk$
VWait 100
NPrint " "
NPrint "Enthusiasm is now set to 200"
NPrint "Click to continue"
MouseWait
*nar\F0enthusiasm=200
Speak Spk$
VWait 100

NPrint " "
NPrint "Perturb is now set to 200"
NPrint "Click to continue"
MouseWait

*nar\F0perturb=200
Speak Spk$
VWait 100

Speak "I am really perturbed!"
VWait 50

NPrint " "
NPrint "Click to exit"
MouseWait
End



--BOUNDARY.1748545192.1

