@NODE "Mail_438" "Re: narrator.device - v37 features"
From: "Linda Bell" <zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: Re: narrator.device - v37 features
Date: Sun, 20 Jun 1999 11:30:01 +0100
X-UIDL: c72a052456270ae43ab3d536e4279af0

Thanks for all that Curt - I did know, though, I was just warning other
people.  No I didn`t change the bytes to words in the newvoice structure,
but I am saving the records to file, and only some of the values are UBYTEs,
so you have to be careful which you AND with $FF, as some are +/-100, while
others are 0-255.

The annoying thing was that the V36 variables were WORDS.

VIC

BTW - I mentioned in passing to my brother that I was updating Mr. Wolf (the
cheeky speaking clock) and he said my sister-in-law got a watch for
Christmas, that speaks the time, or sometimes says something rude instead.
I wish people that I`ve never met would stop nicking my ideas!




