@NODE "Mail_440" "NCS & Debugger clash?"
From: Leigh Parry <lparry@free4all.co.uk>
Date: Fri, 25 Jun 1999 08:41:07 +0000
Subject: NCS & Debugger clash?
X-UIDL: 36cd39f46601213bb0905778a5abab8d

--BOUNDARY.20455728.2

Hello,

If I 'compile & run' the attached file and quit out of the debugger i have no
problem, but uncomment the ';NInitScreen 0' line an then 'compile & run', quit
from the debugger again and 'PANIC' stays up & cli on WB stay open.

Anyone else have this problem ? How do I solve it ?

Cya,

    Leigh.

-- 
<sb>
<sb>Leigh Parry
<sb>EMail: lparry@free4all.co.uk
<sb>URL: www.free0024068.free4all.co.uk
<sb>
<sb>Smile - People will wonder what you're thinking.
<sb>
--BOUNDARY.20455728.2
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="wierd-freeze"

DEFTYPE .l

WBStartup

Stop

; when debugger comes up quit out. no PANIC & cli closes down

;NInitScreen 0

; Uncomment this and re-run, when debugger quit PANIC & cli remains open

Delay_250
End



--BOUNDARY.20455728.2

