@NODE "Mail_447" "New Prog Crashes my miggy :(("
From: Bippy M <BippyM@stingent.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Sat, 12 Jun 1999 23:50:37 +0000
Subject: New Prog Crashes my miggy :((
X-UIDL: 344f3c947335b41e5f8a41a96f89fb96

--BOUNDARY.19498712.3

Hiya Guys,

seeing as no one answered my last mail, i'll re-send it.. if anyone has any
ideas PLEASE speak up.....


A friend has asked me to write a small program that examins team files from
swos and allows you to search for a player, and then reports back the
team(s) the player was found in.

I've written a quick prog that does this but... it a). crashes when you
quit/end and b). if you select to go again, it doesn't display the teams!!

Also is there a better way to load the file, I'm using memory banks as
readile etc.. causes even more probs than above.

Attached is the source (It's messy, so don't expect much!!) to test it
you'll need a swos team file (one attached) and XFD Library installed with
XFDDecrunch in c:

Thanx..
T'ra
-- 
x----------------| BippyM@Stingent.freeserve.co.uk |-----------------x
|                                                                    |
|  Current Projects:                                                 |
|                    Overflow (Pipemania Clone) [..^.......] 30%     |
|                    Packer2Packer Suite        [.^........] 20%     |
|                                                                    |
x----------------| BippyM@Stingent.freeserve.co.uk |-----------------x

--BOUNDARY.19498712.3
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="findplr.asc"
Encoding: binary

ver$="$VER: FindPlayer v1.0 (05-06-1999) "+Chr$($a9)+"1999 M Green"

WBStartup:FindScreen 0

; Search through all the files in a team dir for the requested player"

; Brings up a requester...

Dim mk$(5000)
Dim prog$(5000)

Dim founds$(50000)

RTEZSetPattern 0,"team#?"
jj.l=0
f$=""
ret.l=RTEZMultiLoadFile ("Select Teams")
   Window 0,10,10,400,100,$100e,"Looking for Player : "+plr$,0,1
   WLocate 10,10:Print "Please Wait this could take time!!!!"
i.l=0
  If ret

    mk$(i)=RTNextPathEntry

    ; Code in here loads the file, depacks it to ram using XFD-Decrunch
    ; and then re-loads it and checks it..
    path$=GetPathName (mk$(i))
    NPrint path$
    While mk$(i)<>""


    mk$(i)=GetFileName (mk$(i))
    NPrint mk$(i)
    succ.l=CopyFile (path$+mk$(i),"Ram:"+mk$(i))
    i+1
    JSR decrunch
    mk$(i)=RTNextPathEntry
    jj+1
  Wend


  EndIf
  CloseWindow 0
  JMP process

.decrunch

WLocate 10,30:Print "Decrunching file "+mk$(i)
Execute_ "C:xfddecrunch ram:"+mk$(i),0,0
WLocate 10,30:Print SPACE$(60)
RTS

.process

  body$="Please enter EXACTLY the name of the player"+Chr$(10)+"you wish to look for"
  plr$=RTEZGetString("Find Player",body$,"_Search")

  plr$=UCase$(plr$)
  Window 0,10,10,400,100,$100e,"Looking for Player : "+plr$,0,1
  NPrint "Please wait... This could take a long time!!!!"

  pos.l=-1

  For i.l=0 To jj

    lenfile.l=Exists("ram:"+mk$(i))
    numteams.l=lenfile/684

    LoadBank 0,"ram:"+mk$(i)
    mempos.l=Bank(0)
    ofsett.l=7

    succ.l=PICreateRequest("Please Wait....Searching "+mk$(i),0,numteams)


    For k.l=0 To numteams-1

        team$=Peek$(mempos+ofsett)


        pass$=Peeks$(mempos+ofsett,683)

        WLocate 10,10:Print SPACE$(60)
        WLocate 10,10:Print "Searching "+team$:VWait:VWait

        pos.l=Instr(pass$,plr$)

        If pos.l>0

          NPrint "Found Occurance!!"
          founds$(found.l)=team$
          found.l+1

        EndIf

       ofsett+684
       succ.l=PIUpdateRequest (k)
    Next k

    FreeBank 0
    PIEndRequest
  Next i

  body2$="Found "+plr$+" in the following Teams:"+Chr$(10) : body$="" : ok$="_More"
    k=0
  For i=0 To found-1
    body$+Chr$(10)+founds$(i)

    If k=>10
      JSR req
      k=0 : body$=""
    EndIf

    k+1

   Next i

   body2$="Total Occurances of Player : "+plr$+" was - "+Str$(found):body$="":ok$="_Search Another|_Goodbye!":JSR req

   Select a.l
    Case 0: Even:End
    Case 1: For i=0 To found:founds$(i)="":Next:CloseWindow 0:JMP process
   End Select

End

.req
  a.l=RTEZRequest("Success or Failure!!",body2$+body$,ok$)
RTS




--BOUNDARY.19498712.3

