@NODE "Mail_449" "Re: New Prog Crashes my miggy :(("
From: Rob Hutchinson <loki@sds.in2home.co.uk>
Date: Sun, 13 Jun 1999 13:31:12 +0100
Organization: Satanic Dreams Software.
Subject: Re: New Prog Crashes my miggy :((
Encoding: binary
X-UIDL: d92deec7c0344aaa9b2fc9454e0a6328

Hello Linda
     Hiya, Linda... ,on 13-Jun-99 you mailed me about: Re: New Prog Crashes my miggy :((! So I`ma reply`in...

[=> I`ll have a look at your source - but that seems to be the only thing
[=> attached.

Yup, I noticed that.

[=> If I figure it out, I`ll get back to you.

K, well, I just wanted to add that I think it`s due in some way to one
of the blitz memory reading commands.. Peek, PeekTo$ Peeks$...

I was writing a program not long ago that would load a file into a
bank and then PeekTo$ along it in steps of 2 bytes.. Occasionally
for no reason I could see, when the program terminated it crashed
in EXACTLY the way yours does Bippy. I tried replacing PeekTo$ with
Chr$(Peek.l) etc... etc. but the same errors occured. In the end I
removed the bank loading and peeking stuff and used Inkey$(2)
on the file and I`ve not had a problem since.. For you it`s easier
though cos it happens every single time. And you will know when
you figure it out.

As it only happens on exit of the program, I would suggest it`s something
to do with freeing the back. You could try replacing the bank stuff
with AllocMem_ And FreeMem_ .. But always remember to free the mem
when you exit. If that works your laffing... Failing that, try commenting
all your memory reading commands just to check if it`s one of those.
Commenting is one of the most effective ways to debug code :).
Just comment all the stuff that wont stop it from reaching the
end of the code.. Even if it`s not doing anything,.. If it finished
execution without crashing, start uncommenting the lines one by one
until you find the bitch. Then all you have to work out it why :) heheh

[=> 
[=> 
Regards
-- 
