@NODE "Mail_453" "No ACIDLIBS"
From: Leigh Parry <lparry@free4all.co.uk>
Date: Sun, 20 Jun 1999 01:22:39 +0000
Subject: No ACIDLIBS
X-UIDL: 7592bdd27751503fa5fbbb350d31e1db

Hello,

I haven't got an ACIDLIBS file in by Blitz drawer, some time ago I wrote a
prog that split it into it's seperate Libs, which are then stored in
'Blitzlibs:Basic/' + 'Blitzlibs:System/'. I have those libs then converted
into my Deflibs file size 494444. I found it easier to then update the faulty
libs or change them. I would like to know if I Shouldn't do this as I haven't
had any problems with this way. It may cause probs I'm unaware of though.

I would also like to know how feasible it would be to seperate any big libs
into smaller 'command' files which could then be 'Included', this might then
produce smaller compiled executables, as only the commands used would be
included. Any 'Included' file which needs others in its 'Parent' lib could
then include that file. (exclusivily including libs only one).

This would drastically reduce filesizes, especially when big 'Lib' files are
used,   

Any thoughts?

Cya,

    Leigh.

-- 
