LP > would be included. Any 'Included' file which needs others in its 'Parent'
LP > lib could then include that file. (exclusively including libs only one).

In my oppinion this is the way any programming language should work.
In fact this should be the work of the compiler, preparse the code, check the
commands and the libs it needs and fetch the minimum required for those libs to
work...

LP > This would drastically reduce filesizes, especially when big 'Lib' files
LP > are used,

Obviously :)

-- 
Best Regards,

Rui Carvalho «gRiM»

