--BOUNDARY.20200816.1

Hello,

I have a problem (well more than one, but we won't go into them ;-)

how can i prevent the following code from causing an enforcer hit , this code
is similar to some in a prog i'm working on and I believe the only Enforcer
hits are caused by this code. ( AGARed ,etc.)

How else colud i stor the pointer colours withouth having to go into too much
depth ( I might drown ;-)


Cya,

    Leigh.

-- 
<sb>
<sb>Leigh Parry
<sb>EMail: lparry@free4all.co.uk
<sb>
<sb>Smile - People will wonder what you're thinking.
<sb>
--BOUNDARY.20200816.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="disp_pointer_cols"


DEFTYPE .l

WBStartup
WBenchToFront_
WbToScreen 0
dum=AGARed(16)
mpr17=AGARed(17) : mpg17=AGAGreen(17) : mpb17=AGABlue(17)
mpr18=AGARed(18) : mpg18=AGAGreen(18) : mpb18=AGABlue(18)
mpr19=AGARed(19) : mpg19=AGAGreen(19) : mpb19=AGABlue(19)
NoCli

Window 0,5,50,300,100,$1f,"Pointercols",-1,-1

Format "###"

NPrint  "     Red    Green    Blue"
NPrint  "17   ",Str$(mpr17),"     ",Str$(mpg17),"     ",Str$(mpb17)
NPrint  "18   ",Str$(mpr18),"     ",Str$(mpg18),"     ",Str$(mpb18)
NPrint  "19   ",Str$(mpr19),"     ",Str$(mpg19),"     ",Str$(mpb19)
MouseWait
End



--BOUNDARY.20200816.1

