Hi Anton,

>So I'm going to
>try getting the E-Clock rate, but that's accessing the timer device to
>get the TimerBase so I can do the library call- I've got Dave's
>audio.device example to go from, so it shouldn't be too difficult.
>   I could get the rate of the screen (I looked, but couldn't find the
>appropriate offset :-/ , but would that give an incorrect rate if it
>was on a GFX card screen?
>  Does anyone have a timer.device example in blitz by any chance, or
>other suggestions.


Hmmm, well the ReadEClock function returns the frequency of the eclock
(ticks/sec) which is what I assume your after. The only problem is that this
is a function of the timer.device, so you have to open the device, then
pretend it`s a library and call -60 (I think) from the timer device base
address. I think you need to pass a structure in a0 or something for it to
fill the current eclock time in, and returns the frequency in d0, or is it
the other way around...anyway you get the idea.

Dave

P.s. I haven`t got time at the moment to work on the kart game, as I`m
trying to get a demo of TDW finished for WOA, so it`ll be a while before we
can see your marvelous UDP in action :(


