@NODE "Mail_463" "Re: object maximums"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 15 Jun 1999 14:53:21 -0500
Subject: Re: object maximums
X-UIDL: cd47da93152be6a96da73755dd1a7f18

Hi Vic


> Hello ppl,
> 
> As I said earlier, my object maximums appear to be corrupted:
> 
>  Windows      5
>  s         5065
>  ....                     more objects
>  Consoles     5
>  s            0
> 
> 1. Does anyone know where the information for object maximums is stored,
>   so that I can investigate the relevant file?

The individual libraries themselves contain this information.  Well, they
contain the object information anyway.

The actual settings you have set in your source will be in your source's
.xtra file

So, for example, if you have the Windows library on your setup, Windows will
be shown in the object maximums area.  I'm not sure where the default
number comes from, probably from the library also.   
> 
> 2. can you tell me what you have for your object maximums in place of the
>   two "s" above.

In my setup it goes:

Windows
IconInfos
ReqLibs
GTMenuLists
Consoles
TagLists
NChunkys
PTModules

But this could be different, depending on what libraries you have installed.

It sound like one or more of your libraries is corrupted.  I would suggest
copying everything over again, including acidlibs and everything in the
Blitzlibs: drawers, but not deflibs.  Then do a makedeflibs and try again.

IMPORTANT!  Before doing this, load up any source codes you want to keep,
and save them out as ascii, just in case the tokens change on you...

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



