On 14-Jun-99, Dave wrote:
 
> Just want to pick some peoples brains...a friend has offered me a
> laptop (pc) with xircom Global Access Credit Card Ethernet and Modem
> 33.6. Will this work with the pc card work with the amiga?? The manual
> say`s it`s pcmcia 2 compatible (it doesn`t say if it is 2 or not, just
> that it`s compatible) and the amiga says something like pcmcia 2 (or
> was it the big C`s idea of pcmcia 2??). Anyway I borrowed and
> naturally whacked it in, and all it does is freeze my miggy. It
> doesn`t crash, just like pauses everything (even dma) until I take it
> out again. Is that normal?? (yeah..ok!) or is my miggy`s port bust, or
> the modem (I didn`t borrow the laptop to test it) or just a wonderful
> compatability problem??

  All I know, is that some Credit card modems/memory have the pins
offset at an angle (I think it's the Toshiba system), and the Amiga has
them in line with each other- you can check by looking at the pins in
the miggy, and the holes in the card- I doubt wether you could push it
in, if it was like that- but you never know :-/

-- 
