@NODE "Mail_473" "Re: Off topic but amiga related problem"
X-Originating-IP: [194.238.50.17]
From: James Jaffrey <jamffrey@hotmail.com>
Subject: Re: Off topic but amiga related problem
Date: Mon, 14 Jun 1999 01:51:35 PDT
X-UIDL: 56fa37c317e33179e3678f6d4ee12c5b

Hi Dave,

>Just want to pick some peoples brains...a friend has offered me a laptop
>(pc) with xircom Global Access Credit Card Ethernet and Modem 33.6. Will
>this work with the pc card work with the amiga?? The manual say`s it`s
>pcmcia 2 compatible (it doesn`t say if it is 2 or not, just that it`s
>compatible) and the amiga says something like pcmcia 2 (or was it the big
>C`s idea of pcmcia 2??). Anyway I borrowed and naturally whacked it in, and
>all it does is freeze my miggy. It doesn`t crash, just like pauses
>everything (even dma) until I take it out again. Is that normal??
>(yeah..ok!) or is my miggy`s port bust, or the modem (I didn`t borrow the
>laptop to test it) or just a wonderful compatability problem??


If you remember back in the old days when 16-bit memory was available for 
PCMCIA slots there is every possibility that your miggy thinks that the 
PCMCIA modem is a memory card and is trying to use it as such.
PCMCIA modems were never designed with our superior miggy's in mind, so 
maybe it does something that your poor miggy doesn't like.
Just out of interest, how were you planning on using the modem when as for 
as I am aware there are no drivers for PCMCIA modems?
If you know otherwise I'd like to know because a friend of mine would like 
to fit one to his A600.

I am definitely no expert, but this is a distinct possibility.


Jamffrey (jamffrey@hotmail.com)

