@NODE "Mail_474" "Re: Off topic but amiga related problem"
From: "Dave" <dave@nbsamiga.demon.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Off topic but amiga related problem
Date: Mon, 14 Jun 1999 17:21:15 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 3f121971ba4556f33d01bd95da87ab95

Hi James,

>If you remember back in the old days when 16-bit memory was available for
>PCMCIA slots there is every possibility that your miggy thinks that the
>PCMCIA modem is a memory card and is trying to use it as such.
>PCMCIA modems were never designed with our superior miggy's in mind, so
>maybe it does something that your poor miggy doesn't like.
>Just out of interest, how were you planning on using the modem when as for
>as I am aware there are no drivers for PCMCIA modems?
>If you know otherwise I'd like to know because a friend of mine would like
>to fit one to his A600.


There is a generic one on aminet, but I have seen some docs, and I assume I
could just write a driver for it if the generic one doesn`t work. I`m sure
that all it was designed for originally was memory (silly idea, cos anything
for a laptop costs more than normal stuff..like 2.5" ide harddrives!), but
I`m sure there are some people out there using this port for something other
than that. A friend suggested that it might be type 1 compatible only, but
that`s not what commodore said, but then, they said a lot of things!!

>I am definitely no expert, but this is a distinct possibility.


I don`t think anyone is, this has to be the most underused expansion port on
the amiga. I`m sure the main problem is drivers..but there are no lists of
compatible pc card products, so even if I wanted one, I wouldn`t know which
to buy.

Thanks anyway,

Dave


