>> Just want to pick some peoples brains...a friend has offered me a laptop
>> (pc) with xircom Global Access Credit Card Ethernet and Modem 33.6. Will
>> this work with the pc card work with the amiga??
>
>No. The modem part, maybe with the PCMCIA modem driver on Aminet might,
>with some luck. The NIC - forget it.


I would be able to write my own driver, but all I was really after was the
33.6k modem..anything I transfer to my pc is either small enough for floppy
or big enough for me to use twin express, but it`s a shame we can`t use
ethernet on the amiga without paying silly money (I picked up my pc ethernet
isa card for 5 ukp).

>> all it does is freeze my miggy. It doesn`t crash, just like pauses
>> everything (even dma) until I take it out again. Is that normal??
>> (yeah..ok!) or is my miggy`s port bust, or the modem (I didn`t borrow the
>> laptop to test it) or just a wonderful compatability problem??
>
>The latter most likely. But it shouldn't freeze, it should just
>refuse to work. When you say pause, do you mean a complete
>stand still or "just" that everything runs in slow-motion? If the
>latter, check with the PCMCIA-tool that shipped with OS 3.x to
>see if it senses something is present at all.


Well that`s the odd point. Whenever I plug it in, immediately it freezes.
Whatever it`s doing it stops (be it during reboot, or powerup or midway
through loading wb). It doesn`t go slow, just stops until I take it out
again. I checked the tool, and when I insert it, then window clears (as if
it`s going to refill with the data from the card) but it never does as it`s
frozen, and then I take it out and it goes back to normal. I`m wondering if
my amiga querys it for information and it doesn`t send the right messages
back, or doesn`t init properly (the only other answer is my ports bust..but
I`ll have to wait to test it on another amiga).

Thanks for trying

Dave


