> Thanks, I`ll have a look.  I`ve been trying to follow the brief instructions
> in the autodocs, and the docs on the narrator that I downloaded from `that
> site`, but these docs tell me to use the extended form of the
> CreateIORequest - which they refer to as CreateExtIO - which doesn`t appear
> to exist according to Blitz or my autodocs.

CreateExtIO is a function from amiga.lib (which if you don't know is a link lib 
for C compilers) and so you can't use the commands with Blitz. Unless soemone 
writes a way of reading in the .lib file. I had problems when I tried to 
convert a C program which used the audio.device as it also used one of the 
functions. The bad thing was that the BeginIO function (one in amiga.lib) does 
not clear the flags of the IORequest structure, but apparently all the 
functions I could use did. And I needded to use the flags :(


