  Well, after playing Quake multiplayer over the net (and getting killed
lots by amorel! ;), I've found being able to multitask is awesome! I
can have IRC and STRICQ up and running, and if anyone wants to contact
me while I'm playing Quake they can (only if I want them to of
course!). The other day I was playing Quake multiplayer while while
waiting for someone to turn up on #Blitz on IRC on the regular Sat
night session. I was playing for about half an hour before Chris turned
up on IRC. The Quake screen flashed, so I knew someone had turned
up :-) If my GF needs to get hold of me in a hurry while I'm playing a
multiplayer game, she can just ICQ me and the ICQ screen and Window
will pop forward with the message- it's really amazing!! (It usually
gets me killed, but hey :)
  Quite often playing Quake, I remember something I meant to do on the
computer, and if I don't go and do it at that moment, I will forget
again. So I can just go (maybe go hide in a dark corner if I'm playimg
online :) and flip screens to the Dopus screen (which I always have
up), fix the prob, and go back to my game. Sometimes I do this if I
don't know the map very well (or need to have a look at the
TeamFortress docs), I can have a quick look at the readme, and just
flip back to Quake and carry on! 
  I don't think you could do this multi-player on a PC, as the Quake
game would probably be frozen, and I don't know if ICQ would be running
in the background in VESA mode! This is something the Amiga is
excellant at, and should be pushed as a feature! Someone please correct
me if I'm wrong here as I don't know PCs that well :-)  What I want to
do with my net game, is be able to display any messages from say ICQ
(through Arexx) to be printed out like my game messages, so you could
still be contacted, but it wouldn't interrupt your game! This is a
*True* Active Desktop, something a PC user could only /Dream/ of! 
  Any game now that I play, that doesn't multi-task, I find very /very/
annoying! 

