Hi Anton,

On 24-Jun-99, you wrote:

>  Well, the only think I could think of is increase the amount of
> colours- say 24 bit- then remap each palette to the 24 bit one,
> creating a lookup table for each colour.

This is the only solution that I can see....but you wouldn't need any lookup
tables or anything....their are special functions in CyberGraphX for
automatcially remapping the palette to the True/High colours screens.

Then again, if the frames are 16Bit themselves you wouldn't need any remap
them at all....two problems with this one though, they would be limited to
Graphics card users and it would be twice as slow as the 8bit frames (16bit
= twice the size)

Good idea though ;)

