> This is the only solution that I can see....but you wouldn't need any
> lookup tables or anything....their are special functions in CyberGraphX
> for automatcially remapping the palette to the True/High colours screens.

Not wanting to appear thick, but I probably will, couldn't you do this, similar 
to what Mr Burkey done with Foundation.

Double buffer the screen by making it twice as big and flipping between halfs. 
Update the palette after you flip.

While anim_not_finished
    Draw next frame to hidden half
    WaitTOF_ (or other kind of delay)
    Flip to display half of screen just drawn on
    Change to new palette
Wend

It would eliminate some flicker as you won't get things change while you draw. 
You'd maybe get some flicker though, because of the fact that you are still 
changing palette.

Isn't there any way to remap the frames to the same palette and only use the 
palette change function when it needs to be, i.e. on the start frame of a new 
sequence of frames?


