@NODE "Mail_518" "Re: Point and Plot."
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Sun, 20 Jun 1999 14:41:12 -0500
Subject: Re: Point and Plot.
X-UIDL: a57750100ccf8620a0c01e2bec25d4da

Hi Thomas

On 20-Jun-99, Thomas Cobb wrote:
> Rob Hutchinson wrote:
> 
>> That is why it takes so long.
>> 
>> What was the point in this then? To reduce memory that the Bitmap takes
>> up?
> 
> No, the bitmap is still taking up the same amount of space.

Well, it only takes up the same memory space if it is 256 colours (8
bitplanes) Less colours and it does use less memory, and is therefore
faster to draw, etc. 

An 8 bit Chunky uses a whole byte for each pixel, no matter how many colours
you are using.

Also, this allows Dual Playfield (2 bitmaps moving independantly of each
other, but shown as if it was one bitmap)

Other effects are also possible, by altering only certain bitplanes. 


                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
