@NODE "Mail_520" "Re: Point and Plot."
From: Sami =?iso-8859-1?Q?N=E4=E4t=E4nen?= <sami.naatanen@dlc.fi>
Date: Mon, 21 Jun 1999 22:53:41 +0300
Subject: Re: Point and Plot.
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: c00c0b811234976f557b1b371525a1db

On 19-Jun-99, Rob Hutchinson wrote.

>  Hello, and what not,
>  
>     Is there a faster way to point/plot? Has anyone got a faster ASM
>  way to do this? Or another lib that does this job better?
>  
>  Failing that, does anyone know how these commands work? 
>  I think it`s just determining the offset inside the bitmaps data
>  from the X/Y coords and then peeking the RGB values????
>  Anyone know the structure of the raw bitmap data?
>  
>  The point and plot command in blitz are the slowest 2 gfx commands
>  I`ve seen to date!! Esspecially for what they do!!. Just 1 sodding
>  pixel man :(
>  
>  Any ideas anyone?

Well as litle asm statement, but it isn't much faster than the original
acid one, I think. This is purely, because this kind of thing can't be done
in many different and fast ways. due to the nature of bitmaps.

statement plotti{BMap.l,x.w,y.w,col.b}
  move.l d0,a0
  move.w EBWidth(a0),d0    ; not sure about the size (word?)
  mulu.w d0,d2
  move.w d1,d0
  and.w  #f,d0
  and.l  #fff0,d1
  add.l  d1,d2
  moveq  #0,d1
  move.b Depth(a0),d1    ; not sure about the size (byte?)
  subq.w #1,d1
  move.l Bmap(a0)+,a1    ; if I remember correctly this offset is eight
loop
  bclr.w d0.w,(a1,d2)
  btst.b d1,d3
  beq clear

  bset.w d0.w,(a1,d2)
clear
  move.l Bmap(a0)+,a1
  dbra   d1,loop
  asmexit
end statement

Most probably wont work, and personaly I'm not very interested about planar
GFX because it's quite limited in pixel prefect drawings.
Anybody tought how fast would DPaintV be, if all GFX would be rendered in
chunky and then delta c2p -> planar? :(

-- 

            Sami Näätänen   A1260 50MB 4.5GB 2X 56k HP LaserJet4L
            EMail: sami.naatanen@dlc.fi



