@NODE "Mail_521" "Re: Point and Plot."
From: Mikkel =?iso-8859-1?Q?L=F8kke?= <flameduck@software.dk>
Date: Mon, 21 Jun 1999 06:28:40 +0200
Organization: M2 productions
Subject: Re: Point and Plot.
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 8c00cb568d7e9d303d59fd5d5550d1a2

Hello Rob.

You wrote:

>   Is there a faster way to point/plot? Has anyone got a faster ASM
> way to do this? Or another lib that does this job better?

!!! MILDRED !!!

> Failing that, does anyone know how these commands work? 
> I think it`s just determining the offset inside the bitmaps data
> from the X/Y coords and then peeking the RGB values????
> Anyone know the structure of the raw bitmap data?

Yes, it goes something like this. 1st bitplane bitmap - 2nd bitplane bitmap, aso depending on how mny bitplanes you have.

> The point and plot command in blitz are the slowest 2 gfx commands
> I`ve seen to date!! Esspecially for what they do!!. Just 1 sodding
> pixel man :(

Yes, but on the lovely nd brilliant amiga, displays are in planar, so you have to take 1 bit from 8 differents bytes (for an 8 plane display), in different loctions, and calculate the value.

> Any ideas anyone?

I suggest moving to a chunky library, like Mildred, or the NCS. It's a bit slower at rendering stuff, and requires min 030. But you can have everything in FAST ram, and do all kinds f specil effects, really really fast. See the Mildred homepage for some examples.


Greets,
-- 

