@NODE "Mail_527" "Re: Pointy things, or the plot thickens!"
From: Donovan Reeve <bubby.lnk@ispi.net>
Date: Wed, 30 Jun 1999 21:27:25 +0500
Subject: Re: Pointy things, or the plot thickens!
X-UIDL: a411451b41be59b6b2483c8e09f7f307

On 01-Jul-99, Tony Rolfe flashed:
>It's been a long time since Donovan Reeve said these things, but I've
>been away for a few days.
>> The Boxer, which I have had on order for over a year, will be
>> capable of being upgraded to a NG Amiga (a recent developement) and
>> also has removed the 2mb chip-ram limitation (another recent
>> developement).  These things combined with the addition of PCI slots
>> and a change to high speed DIMMs instead of SIMMs all have changed
>> the character of the machine a bunch!

>I'm not doubting what you've said for a minute, but where did you get
>this lovely news?   I also "expressed an interest" in the Boxer over a
>year ago (they wouldn't let me place an order), but they have told me
>nothing and their web site was last updated in February!   

>I'd love to be able to tap into that source of Info.



  I live in the U.S.A. where a phone call to Anti-Gravity (The Western
Hemisphere Boxer builders and distributers who are working closely with
Access on the Boxer)is free.  They are friendly folk, and I have had
many long talks with their personel, including their tech people and the
owner.  They are very open and honest, and keep me updated well, the
good and the bad.  Of course the only real bad is that I can't have
mine yet.  The good is that they keep uping the annie on the spechs
and performance.  It's easily twice the machine it was to be a year ago.

  I won't be able to use that extra 16mb simm I have laying around in it
now, but I really didn't want to wast a ram slot on 16mb anyway as I
now plan to put a minimum of 160mb in it to begin with and not too much
later yank the 32mb dimm it will come with and go to a full 512mb fast
ram to deal with some graphics I am becoming involved with.  Also, I
have need to get into vidio soon and this machine will be my host for
that as well.


cacha later,

Donovan Reeve (bubby.lnk@ispi.net)



