@NODE "Mail_528" "Power Basic Examples ;))"
From: Daniel Allsopp <daniel@thesnakepit.demon.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 30 Jun 1999 01:29:24 +0100
Subject: Power Basic Examples ;))
X-UIDL: 1e2b02e4f8182fde55b5c87250e6d483

Hi Fred,

Any chance you can send those PB examples and code to the list or me
directly? I can't wait to see what it's capable of.

I'd like to ask a couple of question if I may, as it might affect my decision
to continue with writing my game Blitz instead of switching to C++.

1) Can PB compile code for specific 68K processors? i.e. special faster
versions for 040 or 060.

2) How easy is it to import BB2 code into the compiler. Is there a converter
or will it require major rewrites for PB?

3) Will there be an option to use Blitz Libraries? i.e. Mildred for PB or
would Mildred have to be re-written specifically for PB?

Thanks for your answers ;)

-- 
Cheers,
    Daniel

<tsb>E-Mail: daniel@thesnakepit.demon.co.uk
<tsb>URL: http://www.thesnakepit.demon.co.uk/
<tsb>ICQ Number : 20783863
