@NODE "Mail_529" "Re: Power Basic Examples ;))"
Date: Wed, 30 Jun 1999 10:41:38 +0200
From: Frederic Laboureur <alphasnd@sdv.fr>
Subject: Re: Power Basic Examples ;))
X-UIDL: 31ad52d1796e0041926308a910370bd1

--=====================_930724898==_
Encoding: quoted-printable


	Hello Daniel,

>Any chance you can send those PB examples and code to the list or me
>directly? I can't wait to see what it's capable of.

	Ok, ok.. I've attached to this mail a little archive with 3 code
and executables :

	- Blitz2 standard
	- Blitz2 + NCS
	- PowerBasic

	Quickly, Blitz2 produce 29000 byte exec, NCS, 12000 and PowerBasic 4060 :)
You could look how is the PowerBasic syntax. It's very close to Blitz one.

>I'd like to ask a couple of question if I may, as it might affect my=
 decision
>to continue with writing my game Blitz instead of switching to C++.

	Interresting...

>1) Can PB compile code for specific 68K processors? i.e. special faster
>versions for 040 or 060.

	Not with the first version... BUT the PowerBasic could, yes. BTW, it use=
 the
phxass 680x0 assembler, so it support any assembler instruction and can
do little optimization for 020+ processor. And you could write 040 special
PowerBasic sub library is you want (c2p, fast move...)

>2) How easy is it to import BB2 code into the compiler. Is there a=
 converter
>or will it require major rewrites for PB?

	It's very easy to switch from one to other. Count about half day for a=
 large
code...

>3) Will there be an option to use Blitz Libraries? i.e. Mildred for PB or
>would Mildred have to be re-written specifically for PB?

	Definitely NO. Because the structure of them isn't the same at all. PB one
is much more complex.

>Thanks for your answers ;)

		You're welcome !

				Goodbye,

                        Fred.

