@NODE "Mail_553" "Re: Progress bar"
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Tue, 29 Jun 1999 12:42:17 +0100
Subject: Re: Progress bar
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: da65759be045b4bdb7d74e5d8771b2c7



> How do you make a progress bar with gadtools or something(not mui)? I dont
> think I`ve read anything about that in the docs.

Someone wrote some routines for it a while back. I remember Curt Esser changed 
them slightly, and I think the original author was Tony Rolfe. Apologies to 
whoever if it was not Tony.

Basically, open a window and draw a bar in it, update the bar as you go along 
(also check for events if you have a Stop gadget in the window), close window. 
Everything after that is cosmetic (window backfills, percentage bars, etc).

Probably best to have a procedure to do each of the following:
	open progress indicator
	update bar/check for window events
	close progress bar


-- 
