@NODE "Mail_555" "Re: Progress bar"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 29 Jun 1999 18:18:37 -0500
Subject: Re: Progress bar
X-UIDL: d3d68a046f71042f83d6fd5e052000fe

Hi David

On 29-Jun-99, David McMinn wrote:
> 
> 
>> How do you make a progress bar with gadtools or something(not mui)? I
>> dont think I`ve read anything about that in the docs.
> 
> Someone wrote some routines for it a while back. I remember Curt Esser
> changed them slightly, and I think the original author was Tony Rolfe.
> Apologies to whoever if it was not Tony.

Yes, it was Tony.  I added a double-buffered drawing routine to prevent the
% indication from flickering.
> 
> Basically, open a window and draw a bar in it, update the bar as you go
> along (also check for events if you have a Stop gadget in the window),
> close window. Everything after that is cosmetic (window backfills,
> percentage bars, etc).
> 
> Probably best to have a procedure to do each of the following:
>     open progress indicator
>     update bar/check for window events
>     close progress bar

There is also the NeilsProgressBar library in Blitz which will open a
separate window for you (with optional "cancel" button)

Also, check my "Investigator2" program on my web site for a progress bar
that is part of the main program window - although this one is just a
simple "thermometer" style - bar only, no % readout
> 
> 
Later...
-- 
The days of good English has went.

