@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_556" "Re: Progress bar"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 29 Jun 1999 18:29:12 -0500
Subject: Re: Progress bar
X-UIDL: 1d9b7f5a7448cf6dab71f65c241afdeb

Hi Vic

On 29-Jun-99, Vic E Babes wrote:
>> How do you make a progress bar with gadtools or something(not mui)? I
>> dont think I`ve read anything about that in the docs.
> 
> If I were doing one, I`d simply print blue spaces, using the WJam modes,
> in a bevel box. I was considering this - but considered that during file
> access, it wouldn cause problems, as you would need to keep changing the
> output to the window, and then back to the file - just a thought.

Yes, you would, if you are writing to a file - and printing something to the
window.  If you are just drawing a bar, with Wbox or Wline or something,
you don't.
Printing "space" characters would give a pretty "jumpy" bar, since you could
only update it by the width of the space character each time.  Also, the
width of the space character can vary from font to font.

But either way it won't cause any problems.  I don't think it would even
slow things down by any noticable amount, since file output and input is
buffered.

Later...
-- 
Hackers do it with bugs.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



