@NODE "Mail_558" "Re: Progress bar"
From: Rui Carvalho <grim@ip.pt>
Date: Wed, 30 Jun 1999 07:38:27 +0000
X-SenderInfo: 1; picture="http://www.ip.pt/~ip234558/ddds/grim.gif"; dob=31011977
Organization: Dark Dreams Designs
Subject: Re: Progress bar
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 1ef8719b8e0655f398677b49e6752927

Hello Curt

Somewhere Curt Esser wrote:
CE > Hi Vic

CE > On 29-Jun-99, Vic E Babes wrote:
CE >>> How do you make a progress bar with gadtools or something(not mui)? I
CE >>> dont think I`ve read anything about that in the docs.
CE >> 
CE >> If I were doing one, I`d simply print blue spaces, using the WJam modes,
CE >> in a bevel box. I was considering this - but considered that during file
CE >> access, it wouldn cause problems, as you would need to keep changing the
CE >> output to the window, and then back to the file - just a thought.

CE > Yes, you would, if you are writing to a file - and printing something to
CE > the window. If you are just drawing a bar, with Wbox or Wline or
CE > something, you don't.
CE > Printing "space" characters would give a pretty "jumpy" bar, since you
CE > could only update it by the width of the space character each time. Also,
CE > the width of the space character can vary from font to font.

Common Curt haven't you seen windows? Instead of p.i. why don't we just go for
an animation? 


-- 
Best Regards,

Rui Carvalho «gRiM»

