>> your blits don't hold up the CPU- I assume they'll work with HAM.

> Yup, it IS in Blitz mode. Here's the 'sheer madness' part. PUNCH-SE
> V1.0 is in HAM mode. The amount of memory it needs to work is huge
> from an A500 half CHIP half FAST standpoint, and although I wanted to
> use interleaved bitmaps I came up with a bizarre compromise:

> Each of the two characters (In the Jpeg attachment) are actually 4
> BITPLANES deep, but each SHAPE contains its own pallette to make best
> use of each shape.

>                   .---------------------------------.
>                   |                 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX|
>                   |                 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX|
>                   |                 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX|
>                   |                 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX|
>                   |                 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX|
>                   |                 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX|
>                   |                 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX|
>                   |                 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX|
>                   |                 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX|
>                   `---------------------------------'

> The Coplist is 5 BITPLANES thick, but the program only draws to 4 of
> them. The 5th BITPLANE has the side one characters on clear, the other
> side full, that way each character has a 16 colour palette each. The
> places where they overlap are compensated for by Offset Qblits. The
> actual screen size is about 256x140(?!)
> the rest gets filled up with scoreboards and stuff.

  I don't quite understand what the 5th bitplane does- it sounds
brilliant though :)
 
-- 
        Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
      A500,DF1:,0.5MC,8.5MF,60HDD,WB3.1 &1.3/2.0 
    A1200,2M,CD-Rom,25/040,200/PPC ,WB3.0 
          
