On Fri, 2 Jul 1999, [iso-8859-1] Ayar Baboon wrote:

> rank=Rnd(6)
> ;rank is byte

> What values can this return?

It should return anything between 0 and 6 I think, although without an
INT() around it, it will include decimal places, ie 3.5948533. 

> Which of the returned values are more likely, and can anyone explain
> how my Miggy does random numbers? Surely computers are too stupid to
> pick a number out of a hat? (Not, literally, of course.)

I think the higher numbers tend to appear more often.  Apparently there's
a formula that returns semi-random numbers, ie they are part of a very
long sequence and most people would never notice that, or something.
Don't ask me what the formula is though, I couldn't even start to think
about how it's done. :)

