@NODE "Mail_577" "Re: Reading IFF pictures"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 16 Jun 1999 21:56:11 -0500
Subject: Re: Reading IFF pictures
X-UIDL: 5f301c4aecb2c4d7b6ff9ac228947235

Hi Krzysztof

On 16-Mar-99, Krzysztof Jonko wrote:
> I need some info about reading IFF pictures. Maybe someone have any
> example in BB or assembler?

I have a doc that explains the file format of iff pictures, if you want
that.

> I want to write function to read pictures from inside one big file on CD -
> access only by seek function and maybe some crypt? Thanks for all infos.

An idea for this would be to "cut" the iff headers apart from the actual
picture data on each picture.  Then store the picture data's all in one
place together, and the iff headers together in another place.  Then you
would just need to put the header back on when you load the pictures. 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
