@NODE "Mail_582" "Re: Screen Events"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 01 Jul 1999 18:07:22 -0500
Subject: Re: Screen Events
X-UIDL: b5e72900c393e93cf5c22a9ccbf89ed0

Hi Gaz-JD/FX-s^D

On 01-Jul-99, Gaz-JD/FX-s^D wrote:
> Hi,
>   This has been frying my brain! I've been doing an intro for my new
> gamee (Reservoir Dogz II, coming soon :-) and I while the plot and
> credits are being 'vidi-printed' to the screen (no windows) i need to
> check for mouse button clicks, so that the user can skip thru it all.
> 
> How do I do it?
> 
> I've tried Event=$8 but tha tonly works witha  window presnet
> 
> I've tried WaitEvent but that halts flow, stopping the text from
> appearing, and I've tried searching for a command similar to AM*S's
> MouseKey command.

I have no idea about Amos, but :

If JoyB(0)>0
  (one or both of the mouse buttons is being pressed) 
EndIf

If JoyB(1)>0
  (one or both joystick buttons are down)
EndIf

> Also, would any1 like to beta-test the finished game? It's gonna be
> totally written in Blitz (hopeefully) as I'm trying to draw myself
> away from my fixation with AM*S. :-)

Sure, if it will run on a standard AGA system (no GFX card)
> 
> Could someone also send an example of collision detection between two
> QBlits of the same shape ID? I still ain't worked this out :)

You can use the ShapesHit command (just don't spell it ShapeShit) for this -
yes, it will work fine even if you use the same shape number for both parts
of the command.  It is simply taking the width, height, and handle position
from the shape you specify, as well as the x and y positions you tell it to
see if the two areas overlap.

Later...
