Hi Ayar
On the 01-Jul-99 you said something about Re: Screen Events so now I am going to offer a witty retort (well maybe :)

PQ: Let's see...

Soz. private only. but basically, it goes like this

Repeat
  <Load in next char from file>
  <if its like \ or # or summat, do the associated action 4 that char>
  <make vidi-printer sound>
  <print char to screen>
  <vwait a bit>
Until char=@

And i needed something to let the user stop the sequence, cos
sometimes it takes ages!

PQ: WILL you SHUT UP! ;)

Yes SIR! :=)

PQ: If JoyB(0)<>0
PQ:     skip=True
PQ: EndIf

Doh! Didn't think of JoyB :)

PQ: Repeat
PQ:     ;do a bit of the the intro
PQ: Until All_Done OR JoyB(0)<>0
PQ: 
PQ: Anything wrong with this?

Nope! I dunno how I didn't figure that out myself! Cheers m8.

