@NODE "Mail_590" "Re: Screens..."
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Fri, 11 Jun 1999 05:19:01 -0500
Subject: Re: Screens...
X-UIDL: aa9f7add51f61823e8a77c30417fcdbf

--BOUNDARY.1748395904.1

Hi Rob

On 10-Jun-99, Rob Hutchinson wrote:
> Hello,
> 
>   Erm, this might be a stupid question, but how do you make a screen
> active?. I`ve tried everything from Use Screen to ScreenToFront()..
> But neither seems to work. See attached, you have to click the screen
> first before you can scroll it :(

Yeah, that's simply the way Intuition is set up - there really isn't a
command that will activate a Screen.

You can do it by using the command:

ClickButton 0

after you bring your screen to the front.  This fakes Intuition into
thinking the user clicked on your screen, so it becomes active.

I've also got a function by James Boyd that does this through the OS, if
you'd rather not use the Blitz command.  But it really does the same thing.



                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748395904.1
