No, I think the difference is Frontmost and Active. The active screen is
not nessisarily the frontmost, though only the active screen may take input
from the user. And just cycling thru screens doen`t activate them unless
you click in them. However, even if there is no window on the screen,
it can still be the active screen.

Does anyone know where the active screen information is kept? I checked
the screen stucture but nothing obvious popped out at me :)

