Hi Damir,

On 27-Jun-99, you wrote:

> Hello
> 
> After some experimenting I found out that the problem is solved if I run
> SetPatch before my program. Could it be that when booting without
> startup-sequence the SetPatch gets still executed, or what?

You're probably trying to open an AGA screen before SetPatch is
executed......SetPatch makes your system aware of the AGA chipset. But I
don't think it should work without SetPatch executed.....yet it seems to do
so when you boot with no startup-sequence.....strange.

No idea...

-- 
