Subject: Re: Shapes (Identification, and some other stuff)



> Hello,
> 
>    Does anyone know anything about Blitz`s "Shapes" format?.. 
> Specifically a way to identify a file (a byte-run).. And a way to
> tell how many shapes are in the file..?

The most obvious thing to try, although it probably won't work, is to see =
if 
they are just memory dumps of shapes. Create a shape and look whats inside=
 the 
.shape structure. Then load the file by just readmem'ing it in (with some 
memory allocation for the \_data field). Check if the .shape structure con=
tents 
are the same and if they are, try blitting it.


