@NODE "Mail_621" "Syncing Monitors Answered"
From: Stephen Lebed <slebed@earthlink.net>
Date: Sun, 20 Jun 1999 21:24:11 -0800
Subject: Syncing Monitors Answered
X-UIDL: 49c4b42a9986da4b4f74213426d45612

Hi everyone,

I found out how to sync the VBL of a monitor running through Cybergraphx...

The command is WaitBOVP_(*ScrVP) where *ScrVP is the viewport of the current
screen.

I have used this within the game loop in my program where I would use Vwait.
 With my monitor running at 85Hz my games frames per second locked to
85fps.
I don't know if this command will work on under Picasso96.  Let me know if
it does.

I hope this will help someone out there.

BTW, I have come across a problem with this.  I believe if my program
doesn't finish all its graphics calls by the time the VBL period is over I
get a glitch that sometimes causes my machine to crash... 

Stephen Lebed
slebed@earthlink.net


