@NODE "Mail_626" "Re: Text Readers (WAS Re: My new BUM)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 3 Jun 1999 21:10:07 +0100
From: "Oliver Marks" <oly@enterprise.net>
Organization: Private
Date: 3 Jun 99 21:03:58 +0100
Subject: Re: Text Readers (WAS Re: My new BUM)
Encoding: 7bit

Hi Gareth,
>    I have decided to use an AmigaGuide interface for BUM-NG :-)
> 
> I may still code a new interface in the nr. future, but every attempt
> I make at making a text reader fails miserably. I cannot get my
> program to recognise linefeeds (chr$(10))
> 
> I load in a string of 255 chars from the file (I assume that Blitz
> doesn't carry on on to new lines when reading) and then nprint it out
> to the screen in a window, but it doesn't work, it does it all on one
> line. Any ideas? I know that there is a TextView.bb2 file in the
> Examples dir, but the interface for that is crap, and I can't be
> bothered to alter it.
> 
> Has anyone done a text reader that they want to 'donate' :) It has to
> be quite customisable.
> Cya!

Here a bit of code i just quickly cut out of a program i wrote i hope
it helps it has the code for loading in a text file and how to turn a
window into a text editor.

I am not sure what your problem is but thwe way i did it was to read
each line of the text file into an array so line 1 would go in array 1
line 2 would go in array 2 and so on and then when i displayed the
text i just printed out the array from start to finish using nprint
hope this helps if you do not understand the code just ask and i will
try to help i wrote the code ages ago and have forgot some of it:)

Statement textdisplay{}
    SHARED wind1height
    SHARED html$()
    SHARED count
    windtextsize=wind1height/8
    WindowOutput 1
    WLocate 0,0
    For a=1 To windtextsize
        NPrint html$(a)
    Next a
End Statement

.Wind1
  ;Statement mover{}
  Use Window 1                          ;display text in window 1
  Repeat
  Repeat
    ev.l=Event                          ;store any intuition events
    Select ev                           ;select it
    End Select                          ;if nothing happens exit select
  Until ev=0
  WLocate 0,y*8+1
  EditFrom x                            ;allow user to type in text
    html$(y)=Edit$(html$(y),linelength) ;find line to edit
    x=Editat                            ;store event which exited editing
    Select Event                        ;select the event
      Case 262144                       ;window deactivated
        exit=1                          ;stop editing
      Case 524288                       ;window activated
        exit=1                          ;stop editing
      Case 512                          ;close gadget
        exit=1                          ;stop editing
      Case 2                            ;size changed
      Case 8                            ;mouse click
    ;    xstart=WMouseX/8                ;store text x cordinates
    ;    ystart=WMouseY/8                ;store text y cordinates
    ;    Select WaitEvent                ;wait for something to happen
    ;      Case 8                        ;mouse click
    ;        xfinish=WMouseX/8           ;text end cordinates x
    ;        yfinish=WMouseY/8           ;text end cordinates y
    ;    End Select
    ;    WColour 0,3                     ;highlight text colour
    ;    WLocate xstart,ystart           ;edit position position
    End Select
    Select EditExit                     ;find cause of edit exit

      Case 27                           ;Escape pressed
        exit=1                          ;end editing
      Case 28                           ;cursor up 28
        If y>1 Then y=y-1               ;move up a line
      Case 29                           ;cursor down 29
        If y<lineend Then y=y+1         ;move down a line
      Case 13 ;enter pressed            ;return key pressed
        x=0:y=y+1
        For a=lineend To y              ;repeat until all lines have been moved down
          store$=html$(a)               ;store line 1st line
          html$(a+1)=store$             ;Put first Line into second Line
        Next a
        lineend=lineend+1
    End Select
  Until exit=1                          ;end editing
  textdisplay{}                         ;refresh text display
  Return


.htmlrequester
    filename$=ASLFileRequest$("Select Html Filename",fi$,pa$,"#?.(html|htm",0,0,100,100)
    count=0
    If ReadFile(0,filename$)
    FileInput 0
    While NOT Eof(0)
        html$(count)=Edit$(800)
        count=count+1
    Wend
    Else
    EndIf
    textdisplay{}
    Return

