@NODE "Mail_628" "Re: Text Readers (WAS Re: My new BUM)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Fri, 4 Jun 1999 01:31:01 +0100
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 03 Jun 1999 15:22:43 -0500
Subject: Re: Text Readers (WAS Re: My new BUM)

Hi Gareth

On 03-Jun-99, Gareth Griffiths wrote:

> 
> Has anyone done a text reader that they want to 'donate' :) It has to
> be quite customisable.

There is an example I did of a text reader in a window on my website, and in
Aminet/dev/basic.  (It's the complete source code with lots of comments.)

It actually puts the text file into a GTlistview gadget {for easy automatic
scrollbar & arrows  ;) } and opens a window sized to match the listview
gadget.  The window size is also customizable.  It also does simple
word-wrapping.

It's font-sensitive, and has an optional "topics" cycle gadget
(automatically created by symbols in your text file) to make it jump to
selected parts of the text.

It's also possible to cause selected lines of text to be centered in the
listview.  
If you're interested, check it out.  It's OK to use any or all of it for
whatever you like.

It was originally intended for an online help system for BeatBox2, but we
never used it since we found out how to get Multiview to open on our
program's screen, and I spent quite a bit of time on it, so I'd like to see
it used for something.

The example doesn't show it, but it is pretty simple to also automatically
the topics onto a menu for the "jumping" if you program uses menus.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



