Yes, Indeed, unfortunately it is also ahead of Windoze in crash-prone-ness I have come to the point where as I start MUI applictions, I expect them to crash (If run for longer periods of time, or more of them simultaneously), for no appearent reason, not that Windoze doesn't do this aswell, just not so often, or maybe it's just because I'm more accustomed to PC's crashing than my AMiGA ? But I'll shut up now.

> Screen shots of registered versions on GFX cards look amazing! 

Yeh, but without a GFX card they look bloody horrible with Tragic Workbech colours and "Classic_Marble" everywhere. Sure it was nice back then on the A1200, with no RAM or CPU power, and when the closest you came to customizing Windows was making a new "boot picture". But these days, and with Gnome on the horizon it's pretty sad.


Greets,
-- 

