@NODE "Mail_647" "Re: Text Readers (WAS Re: My new BUM)"
From: Rick Hodger <rick.thehub@bigfoot.com>
Date: Mon, 07 Jun 1999 17:42:29 +0100
Organization: Pagan Software
Subject: Re: Text Readers (WAS Re: My new BUM)
X-UIDL: 08a9050cd75da682a97593be19371036

I watched as Daniel Allsopp hammered "Re: Text Readers (WAS Re: My new BUM)"
out on their keyboard...

>> But the main reason is that I`ve only got 346k free on my Work partition
>> - yes 346k free - however, I`ve just towered my Amiga so that I can get
a
>> big 3.5inch HD, and I`ve just archived everything to floppy in
>> preparation for this. The main reason I would have to have MUI is for
>> DrawStudio - which I didn`t buy when it came out - for the simple reason
>> that it uses MUI - I doubt it is still available.

> Well that is just your stupid fault.....not using one of the best
programs
> on the Amiga because it uses MUI is total stupidity.

> As for your 346k of space left, that your fault again for not upgrading.
> You shouldn't expect people to program for crappy Gadtools when something
> like MUI is available.

Not wanting to start an argument, but he isn't asking anyone to write
Gadtools programs, he just doesn't like MUI, and doesn't have the space for
it.  Fair enough I say, if we were going to force everyone to use certain
pieces of software we may as well just change our names to "Bill Gates"
now.

>> I will give MUI another chance when I get a bigger HD and then let you
>> knnow whether I`ve fallen in love or not. In the meantime, lets not
annoy
>> those who are not interested in this thread by replying back and forth.
>> Naturally those of you that use it have far more experience of it than I
>> do, and are better able to judge its merits - one thing I hate about
>> bragging PC owners is the fact that Windows is generally all they know -
>> but they still feel able to comment on the Amiga - so I apologize. But
>> state again that I feel it is largely cosmetic.

> MUI certainly isn't cosmetic, and one of the reasons I program in MUI is
> because it's piss easy to create a functional GUI. I bet anything you can
> make in Gadtools (which should include auto re-sizable windows, etc etc)
I
> could make in MUI in five minutes....it's not cosmetics, it's the power
of
> exploiting it in programming. It's so easy, with the added advantage that
> the user can customise it to their liking!!

If you read the docs, it's mostly done for two reasons.  It looks nice, and
it makes the programmers life a bit easier.  But all those dozens of files
are needed to make a nice plugin system, you'll find that if everyone
hard-coded a text-editor into their programs you'd find that your overall
hard-disk space would get used up a lot more quickly.  

Vic: By using a series of classes (.mcc) you can use the same code over and
over again for any number of different programs. The .mcp files are for
configuring the looks of your plugins.  That's about it, 

> But, again, it's your choice if you want to miss out on some of the best
> software written for the amiga that otherwise wouldn't exist without MUI.

Exactly.  If he doesn't want to use, don't pressurise him / shout
obscenities about him not upgrading etc.  This has happened all far too
often in the past.

-- 
