@NODE "Mail_660" "Re: Text scrolling"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 2 Jun 1999 00:50:52 +0100
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 01 Jun 1999 18:39:41 -0500
Subject: Re: Text scrolling

--BOUNDARY.1748447832.1

Hi Oliver

On 01-Jun-99, Oliver Marks wrote:
> Hi,
> 
> I manage to write a program that scrolls text thanks for the help but
> it does not scroll it that smoothly and the scrolling seems to be one
> pixel out not sure why any one have any ideas ?

Yes, you have confused the height of the font with the width.
The actual pixel width of each character in the xen.8 font is 6.

Try the attached modification.  It still is not perfectly smooth, but
probably as good as you'll be able to get with this method.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748447832.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="scrolling.asc"


WBStartup
WBenchToFront_
WbToScreen 0

Dim html$(200)
count=0
counter=1
c=0
currchar=1
width=8
Window 0,0,0,600,100,$0001|$0002|$0004|$0400,"Song Scroller",0,1

LoadFont 0,"xen.font",width
WindowFont 0

        If ReadFile(0,"textfile.txt")
            FileInput 0
            While NOT Eof(0)
                html$(count)=Edit$(800)
                count=count+1
            Wend
        Else
          End
        EndIf
        text$=html$(0)
WLocate 0,0
While currchar<=Len(text$) AND Joyb(0)=0
VWait ;40
  WLocate 0,0
  Print Mid$(text$,currchar,30)
  For a=1 To 5
    WScroll 0,0,600,12,1,0
    VWait ;40
  Next a
  a=0
  currchar+1
Wend
MouseWait
End



--BOUNDARY.1748447832.1

