@NODE "Mail_662" "Re: Text scrolling"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Fri, 4 Jun 1999 13:11:50 +0100
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Fri, 04 Jun 1999 07:03:56 -0500
Subject: Re: Text scrolling

Hi Oliver

On 03-Jun-99, Oliver Marks wrote:
> Hi,
> 
>> Yes, you have confused the height of the font with the width.
>> The actual pixel width of each character in the xen.8 font is 6.
> 
> Is there any way to get the fonts width or work it out ?

Yes, a couple of ways.  But it depends if you are using only fixed width
fonts such as xen, or if you are allowing proportional fonts to be used. 
> 
>> Try the attached modification.  It still is not perfectly smooth, but
>> probably as good as you'll be able to get with this method.
> 
> Thanks a lot it is working well enough for what i want :)
> 
> Is there any way to change the colour of the fonts coz i want to have
> some of the words coloured yellow and others black ?
> 
> What other ways of scrolling text are there ?

This all depends on exactly how the program is being done.

Will it run on the WB, or it's own screen?

Is it for a game, where you will be using double buffering and bitmaps?
Or will it be using just the one wimdow?
> 
> How would i modify the code so that it scrolls a hole txt file rather
> than just one line i have been exsperimenting but my attempts have
> stopped the displaying of the text altogether :(

I have a couple of ideas.  But again, it depends on the program.  Will it be
for reading all text files, or just the ones that you supply or that the
program itself makes?

I must go to work now.  But if you can answer these questions, I can get
some ideas back to you over the weekend. 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



