@NODE "Mail_664" "Re: Text scrolling"
From: "David McMinn" <dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk>
Organization: International House of Mojo
Date: Sun, 6 Jun 1999 18:47:34 +0100
Subject: Re: Text scrolling
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: aa458d8d502537ecd933395c6ab22b7a



On 4 Jun 99, at 19:09, Oliver broke out long enough to write:

> I am using fixed fonts i belive they all have .font exstensions i have
> been trying to use a font called bodacious.font which is 74 in height but
> i do not know what the width is

This works for any font, but a fixed width font would be quicker to use width = 
number of chars * width of fixed char. Once your window is open and you have 
done WindowFont x, you can use this

a$="text to scroll"
width = TextLength_(RastPort(0),&a$,Len(a$))

> It is being run in a window on my own screen

You can still double buffer it, although it might not give a better display. 
Depends how much drawing you will be doing per frame.


-- 
