X-UIDL: 7fe08be63eaebc9c743f5456840501ad

>I've just been using David Newton's DLL.bb2 file (Nice one BTW David).


Which version?? The last one I posted was 2.1, and it`s upto 2.3 here (just
some minor alterations)

>I used "Include File" to get the whole .bb2 file into my program, made
>a couple of minor changes, compiled and ran fine.    Then I cut the
>DLL code out of the main program, pasted it into a new window and
>saved it.    It now wouldn't compile!!
>
>I eventually discovered that David had used a variable named start.
>This obviously does not tokenize on his system.  When I included the
>.bb2 file it didn't try to tokenize and when I saved and reloaded my
>program, it didn't tokenize either.


Yep, your right...but it does tokenise when I remove the .l (weird) it`s in
the SEEK_STRINGS asm function, so it doesn`t matter what you call it as I`m
sure you know :).

>When I saved it as a separate file, for some reason it decided to
>tokenize (I do have a Start (Bank) command somewhere).


Yeah..I think it`s because I`m using old ted, not super ted (or something)..

>I just thought I'd mention this - not as a criticism of David - but as
>a warning when passing code around.   Might save someone a bit of
>head-scratching time.


Yeah..very useful. Btw if you make any useful alterations or add functions
lemme know cos I`m using this too :).
(wish it picked it up as a blitz list though...I can force it into a blitz
list array variable but it`s a bit hacky and only lets you add them to
gtlist`s easier, as you still have to use all my list functions for other
things!).

Glad to see somebody else is using it so I didn`t waste my time programming
it,

Dave





