>
>Nothing important, just changed the case for the user functions to
>match the original Blitz ones (ADD_ITEM to Add_Item etc.),
>converted a few functions to statements which handle exception
>conditions themselves (changed function return false to
>Fatal_Error{Mesage$}) and changed all false/true to #False_Flag and
>#True_Flag (Gee I wish I could use better names).


Ahh, I see. I wondered if you needed some list routines I`d missed. I did
plan on adding error messages but I always use a seperate function for that
(ie, if the function returns false, you simply call fetch_last_error which
tells you the error number/string like is usual in C.). I generally stick to
uppercase for function names, capital letters for constants and labels, and
all small for variables as that`s what I`ve done for years (though sometimes
I can`t be bothered!). But everyone has there own system, and your right to
stick to it.

>Just a few things to fit my way of doing things.   Nothing major.


Yep, that`s why I prefer source code includes instead of librarys. If I
change anything or find any bugs, I`ll let you know :) (and I`ll keep track
of any changes that you might need to do).

Dave



