@NODE "Mail_692" "Trogladite Software Plea For Help"
From: "Neil Bullock" <i03427@selby.ac.uk>
        <newsmaster@news-n-stories.de>
Subject: Trogladite Software Plea For Help
Date: Mon, 28 Jun 1999 12:08:12 +0100
Encoding: 8bit
X-Info: Selby College, England
X-UIDL: 70d400d3a0ea7ea3843b25304d190d4c

Hi,
Trogladite Software, as you might know, has gained lots of divisions.
However, we now want to restructure the whole thing. Basically what we need
are teams of people. Below is a complete list of what we need. To apply,
send to trogladite@trogsoft.freeserve.co.uk putting the title of the team
as the subject. If you're reading on the Blitz list, then you might want to
skip down to the developer section, unless you want to have a go at the
others :)

TITLE: Trogsoft Insider Team 
NEEDS: 1x Researcher •1x Writer •1x Graphician 
TASKS: Basically, Trogsoft Insider is the name of the Mailing list which
was announced all those many weeks ago. It's not taken off too well, and we
now want to provide an online version complete with all the important Amiga
news and events, etc. A text version will also be needed to send out to
subsribers. All we now need is a researcher to get the latest Amiga news.

TITLE: Ideas Team
NEEDS: People who have ideas about what programs the Amiga needs
TASKS: This is probably the least demanding of the teams here. Basically,
when you have a good idea about what we could make for the Amiga, send it
to one of the developers at Trogladite Software, and we'll take it from
there. Still need lots of people for this. Remember, all you have to do is
sit at home, look around the web, and everytime you get an idea for a
product, tell us! 

TITLE: Graphics Team
NEEDS: Dedicated 3D and 2D graphicians
TASKS: We've already got a head of the Graphics team, but we need more
people to help with graphics for both games, and applications. If you can
help, PLEASE get in touch. We've got 3 3D graphicians now, and all we need
are 2D graphicians. We'll accept two more and then that'll be it for the
graphics team.

TITLE: Sound Team
NEEDS: People who can record/make high quality IFF sound samples and MEDs
TASKS: This is the team the developers will turn to when they want samples
for their games, or applications. 

TITLE: Developers Team
NEEDS: Some Application Developers Some Games Developers 
	Note that applying for these does not mean you have to only develop 
applications if you apply for application developer. You can do either. 
TASKS: Basically, we want to build up a team of dedicated developers who
basically program things. We're looking for people to join Trogsoft who
would maybe be willing to take over the development of some of our older
products to bring them up to date. 

TITLE: Diskmag Team
NEEDS: A few editors, Several writers, A RESEARCHER (or two)
TASKS: We have taken over The-Point diskmag recently and would like 1
editor and a few writers to keep it going under the Trogladite Software
name. We're also looking for any new ideas for diskmags so we can develop
our Diskmags division ever further. We'd like a few researchers to send us
the latest Amiga news from anywhere they can find it so we can put it in
our magazines.

Note that, if desired, all members of team can get a
firstname.secondname@trogsoft.freeserve.co.uk address 

If you think you could offer your services in any other way then please
also get in touch. Remember that address:
trogladite@trogsoft.freeserve.co.uk and you can still sign up for the
Trogsoft Insider by sending a blank email to tsml@trogsoft.freeserve.co.uk
and don't forget to join the World Of Amiga diskmag eGroup at
http://www.egroups.com/list/woa-dm 

Thanks for reading, 

Neil Bullock
Trogladite Software 

