It sounds to me like you killed your email address that you subscribed
with...very clever, as without it, how can you reply to the unsubscribe
message (a message the blitz list sends to verify your unsubscribe, so
somebody else can not unsubscribe you, as it would fail without the verify
which is how every mailing list i`ve ever been on works), so in fact it is
your fault and not the blitz list. Sending loads of mails back to the list
just increased the amount of bouncing data, so I`m sure your sysop would be
please to see all of them rebound. I assume you didn`t see the replies when
you first asked for help getting off the list, and seeing how their haven`t
been anyother messages from you, we had all assumed you had understood the
simple instructions and removed yourself from the list. Another email
saying..GET ME OFF THE LIST BECAUSE I`M TOO STUPID TO DO IT MYSELF may have
helped, instead of all the silly mails which most people have filtered out
anyway.

I wonder how many people are on the list...(100??) maybe we can vist lots of
freebie sights and sign your email up...if we each did 10+..imagine how much
junk mail you`d receive?? - just a thought....


I don`t think the Amiga world will miss your input one bit,

Dave


P.s. If you want to reply, you`ll need another email address as my server is
set to filter out all junk mail and your mail (same thing!).




