@NODE "Mail_699" "UPD problems -- Please Help!!!!!"
From: Stephen Lebed <slebed@earthlink.net>
Date: Thu, 01 Jul 1999 21:56:26 -0800
Subject: UPD problems -- Please Help!!!!!
X-UIDL: c8c998d2648d602938d7ea0369bcb699

Hi all,

I'm working out the groundwork for my next Amiga game, an internet only
multiplayer space combat game.

I'm trying to test out UPD using the UPD Chat V2.5 with the Blitz extension,
but it won't compile.  I followed the directions for installing UPD, adding
TCPtoBlitz extension, ect, ect.  When I try to compile it, I get a 'Type
Not Found'  error.  It stops on the line

*scr.Screen=Peek.l(Addr Screen(0))

I have Amigalibs.res in the compiler options, but do I need anything else?

Have anyone else got this working on their system?

Is there a conflict with extension numbers or something?

Thanks in advance,

Stephen Lebed
slebed@earthlink.net

p.s.  Is anyone interested in this type of game?   I'm planning on setting
up a dedicated internet connection for it.


