@NODE "Mail_723" "Re: Vblank timer and Ticks GFX card test"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 24 Jun 1999 23:39:42 -0500
Subject: Re: Vblank timer and Ticks GFX card test
X-UIDL: ee77543a6cba0f11c4d8fd886c021b9e

Hi Anton

On 24-Jun-99, Anton Reinauer wrote:

>  Okaley-dokaley here's a little test program to see if the the Ticks,
> and/or Vblank timer run the same under PAL/NTSC, as under a Graphics
> card screen with a different screen rate.

>  Also can someone with NTSC tell me what results they get

I have a NTSC system (AGA only - no GFX card)

I ran it several times with my WB in my usual NTSC hi-res laced mode:

Ticks & VBlanks 3601 ~ 3603


I also reset my WB screen to PAL hi-res-laced:

3031 ~ 3033


Using Degrader to "fool" the system into PAL:

3031 ~ 3033

I hope that helps a bit.
 
-- 
A Smith and Wesson beats four aces.

