@NODE "Mail_725" "Re: Vblank timer and Ticks GFX card test"
From: Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
Date: Sun, 27 Jun 1999 09:55:41 +1200
Subject: Re: Vblank timer and Ticks GFX card test
X-UIDL: 2dc6727f0cbae43762bea7eb69f7db9d

On 25-Jun-99, Curt Esser wrote:
 
>> Okaley-dokaley here's a little test program to see if the the Ticks,
>> and/or Vblank timer run the same under PAL/NTSC, as under a Graphics
>> card screen with a different screen rate.

>>  Also can someone with NTSC tell me what results they get

> I have a NTSC system (AGA only - no GFX card)

> I ran it several times with my WB in my usual NTSC hi-res laced mode:

> Ticks & VBlanks 3601 ~ 3603

> I also reset my WB screen to PAL hi-res-laced:

> 3031 ~ 3033

> Using Degrader to "fool" the system into PAL:

> 3031 ~ 3033
 
>Daniel Allsopp <daniel@thesnakepit.demon.co.uk>

>    Screenmode = 16bit 1024x768
>    51hz, 42,016 Hz

>    Ticks = 3028
>    VWaits = 3028

> Stephen Lebed <slebed@earthlink.net>
 
>I've got 3594 ticks and 3595 vblanks on a 1024x768x16bit display on a
>50mhz060
 
  Well, allowing for the slight variences of the CIA's (in the expected
error), I think we can pretty much say from this, that Graphics Card
screens don't effect the E-Clock (Ticks) or Vertical blank timer- they
obviously both work off the motherboard chips- YAY!!!!
  This means that we can use the vertical blank timer for a long term,
accurate system timer. The E-clock timer could be used as well, but
suffers from the problem that other tasks could change it's value :-( 
With the VBlank timer, it's completely under your control, and you can
reset/adjust your variable as you want, without affecting other
programs :)  Also the code is easy to do- just some Blitz commands!

  Can other people with GFX cards still send me their results direct to
me please, just to make sure :-)  Also if you do, can you tell me what
Card you have, and the screenmode and screenrate- ta :-)

  Coolness- Anton

-- 
 
       Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
      A500,DF1:,0.5MC,8.5MF,60HDD,WB3.1 &1.3/2.0 
    A1200,2M,CD-Rom,25/040,200/PPC ,WB3.0 
          
