@NODE "Mail_730" "Video Format Available For Download"
From: Daniel Allsopp <daniel@thesnakepit.demon.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 23 Jun 1999 15:31:59 +0100
Subject: Video Format Available For Download
X-UIDL: 36f6fa3cfce513dde7f3fc60e9655176


To fix ;)

Well I've 95% finished the video format but there is ONE huge annoying bug
which I can't get rid of.

The damn flickering with "Palette Per Frame".

I'm using CyberGraphX, well I suppose you've read my other mail, and know
what the problem is....if you've got a gfx card could you please run the
example I'm including in the archive to see what I mean.

On anything but an 8Bit 1024x768 screen it flickers.....

Since the archive will be pretty big and pretty useless to people without
gfx cards I'm putting it on my website for people to download.

    http://www.thesnakepit.demon.co.uk/video.lzx

You'll need Fred's XPK library and the xpk.res file, but I've included them
just incase you don't.

It only works on 8Bit CyberGraphX screens, it'll probably crash on >8Bit and
definetly on AGA screens.

Once this is fixed then I'll release the whole thing for people to use in
their own projects, this includes the converter (made in MUI, if you don't
like it tough, make your own ;)) and the player function with AGA support
and AHI.

Please help make this complete......it's soooo close.

-- 
Cheers,
