From: Stephen Lebed <slebed@earthlink.net>
Date: Wed, 23 Jun 1999 21:45:47 -0800
Subject: Video Format test results
X-UIDL: 80ca57e0dd74b3ddff8f2ae44ebe98eb

Hello,

I tested out the video player on my system

A4000T 50mhz060 80meg ram
Cybervision 64 running cybergraphx3


320x240x8 playback - solid and fast except when the planet circled past the
bottom of the frame where a couple of pixels were off color.
640x480x8 -> 1280x1024x8 flickering display playback

1600x1080x8 solid playback again.

Aparently the display is being updated before the previous frame is finish
being drawn.

At 1280x1024x8 the upper half of the image is okay, but the lower half is
flickering.

The frame display is taking longer than one vertical blank period. 

Sorry, I problebly haven't told you anything  you didn't already know...

Kind regards
-- 
Stephen Lebed
slebed@earthlink.net


