@NODE "Mail_743" "Waitevent and loops"
From: bml@thenet.co.uk (Simon Archer)
X-FTN-To: Oliver Marks
Subject: Waitevent and loops
Date: 06 Jun 1999 16:38:59
X-newsreader: Spot 1.3b #1534
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 87114c4f0a93aa6cf59d2f6e5992db55

On 6 Jun 99 Oliver Marks wrote about 'Waitevent and loops'.

 OM> The only way i can get around this is to write the text scroller as a
 OM> seperate program and then load it up on to the current screen.

Personally, I'd set up a timer event to signal your Window's IDCMP port
once every so often to update the text.
By altering the frequency of timer ticks you can alter the speed of the text.

Simon Archer


