Oliver Marks wrote:
> 
> Hi,
> 
> I am testing for window events using select waitevent which stops the
> code until something happens but i want one of the window to have
> scrolling text in it but i do not know how to make the text scroll
> while waiting for something to happen in the other windows.
> 
> The only way i can get around this is to write the text scroller as a
> seperate program and then load it up on to the current screen.
> 
> Anyone know of a better way to get around this problem?

Either use the timer.device, or when you open the window, include
#IDCMP_INTUITICKS in the idcmp flags.  This will give you a
#IDCMP_INTUITICKS event about 10 times a second.

--
