@NODE "Mail_748" "We're on a collision course..."
From: Gareth Griffiths <gaz@jokerd.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Sat, 12 Jun 1999 17:07:01 +0100
Organization: Joker Developments
Subject: We're on a collision course...
X-UIDL: 39493997b2f5c8a5fde10c46cefcba92

Hi,
   In AM*S, each sprite/bob on the screen is given a unique ID which
makes it easy to detect collisions. This doesn't seem to happen in
Blitz.

My GTAclone needs collision more than most games :) and I can't figure
it out. I am testing the game engine at the moment, using LUT's
(cheers Curt!)

Basicaly, there is a car parked stationary on the screen, and your
car. How do I detect collisions between SHAPE 1 (your car) and SHAPE 2
(the other car)

The manual says X,Y parameters are there, but doesn't explain what
they are about. How do I know the X,Y params of a shape if it is
moving constantly? 

Please help, so I can bring GTA to the thousands of Miggy owners out
there :)

Oh yeah, if anyone wants to draw any cars, download gta_dev.lha from
aminet and use the template. 
Cya!
Gaz.
-- 
