>(the other car)
>
>The manual says X,Y parameters are there, but doesn't explain what
>they are about. How do I know the X,Y params of a shape if it is
>moving constantly?


This is easy. You use x,y parameters to differenciated between 2 copies of
the same shape. Say you got shape 2 and blitted it twice, how would it know
which one of the shape 2s to look for collision detection?

You have the x,y co-ords of the car as variables - like XOC and YOC (X
position Of Car and Y position Of Car) and put these as the x, y variables
in the collision command: (CAR=variable for shape number of car and)

if shapeshit (CAR,XOC,YOC,ENEMYCAR,ENEMYXPOS,ENEMYYPOS)=-1 then .....

>Please help, so I can bring GTA to the thousands of Miggy owners out
>there :)


There are other ppl making GTA clones - like me :)

