@NODE "Mail_762" "Re: XBSound & LEShapes libraries"
From: Mikkel =?iso-8859-1?Q?L=F8kke?= <flameduck@software.dk>
Date: Mon, 21 Jun 1999 05:28:09 +0200
Organization: M2 productions
Subject: Re: XBSound & LEShapes libraries
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 0241d3849fed7467094ec7b4d4dea332

Hello Ian.

You wrote:

> I'm desperately seeking two libraries in order to continue development of 
> my Blitz BASIC beat-em-up Legend of the Exploding Fist. They are the XB 
> (or CrossBones) Sound Library and the LE Shapes Library which contains 
> improved shape storage and access commands. Does anyone know where I can 
> find these rare beasts...?

Yeah ! Is that Fist II ? Then *please* send a copy this way !

Anyway, XbonesCIATracker library is one on of the first BUM's as I recll. You should get EML , of Aminet, instead though. The one I have is much better thn the old Xbones, except you have to check to make sure nothing else is using the audio hardware, also, if you want AHI support, someone here did a Digibooster replayer that you could possibly use. I dunno if it does "normal" mods aswell, but you can allways just convert them to DBM.

As for that shape thingy, I got mine with BSS I think it was, havn't used it at all though, since I got Mildred.


Greets,
-- 

