Hello d.boaz@virgin.net.

You wrote:
>     Hmm, I was going to start using this lib also because I`m told
>     it`s more stable on different CPUs but the EML lib I have doesn`t have
>     the decode command which I was using with XBsound, is there a new lib
>     that has this?

>     I reason I want it is because I`m loading the Mod into a bank and
>     then decrypting it then I using decode, is there another way to do this?
>     I can`t save the Mod bank to Ram: and then load with normal command as I`m
>     getting low on mem because datatypes seems to nab loads.

Hrmm, I'm not sure, doesn't it have a cludge function instead ? Anyway, I suppose you could just force it to play the damned thing by tricking it into THINKING it allready loaded the module, It's a bit dodgey, but I guess it would work...


Greets,
-- 

